呂:["口: mouth　丿: katakana no　口: mouth","spine","PHONETIC (ro)","<strong>Spine</strong> connects head and body.","The<strong> spine</strong> goes from one opening mouth/opening (mouth/face) to another mouth/opening (genitals). Just think of these openings being enlarged to represent the head and the body. The bottom is bigger because the body is bigger than the face.","ロ、 リョ","せぼね","呂律 【ロレツ】 articulation<br>ろれつが回らない 【ロレツガマワラナイ】 speaking inarticulately (slurring, lisping, etc.)<br>風呂 【フロ】 bath, bathtub, bathroom, bathhouse, room for drying lacquerware, base (wooden joint connecting the blade of a hoe, spade, etc., to the handle)<br>お風呂 【オフロ】 bath<br>呂 【リョ】 bass range (in Japanese music), six even-numbered notes of the ancient chromatic scale, Japanese seven-tone gagaku scaleimilar to Mixolydian mode (corresponding to: re, mi, fa, so, la, ti, do)<br>呂旋 【リョセン】 Japanese seven-tone gagaku scale (corresponding to: so, la, ti, do, re, mi, fa), similar to Mixolydian mode<br>大呂 【タイリョ】 second note of the ancient chromatic scale (approx. D sharp) (in China), twelfth lunar month<br>仲呂 【チュウリョ】 (in China) 6th note of the ancient chromatic scale (approx. G), fourth lunar month",""],
昌:["日: day; sun　日: day; sun","prosperous","CLEAR, bright","If you work from Sun UP to Sun DOWN you will be<strong> prosperous</strong>.","I kept getting this mixed up with meanings like 'fortune', so here is a fool proof story! Remember the Vulcan salute from 'Star Trek' (a fiction of the sci-fi genre in which heavenly bodies such as SUNS play a huge role) used with the phrase 'live long and PROSPER'? If that's not enough of a visual reminder, the Vulcan salute shows the fingers parted in to 2 sets of 2, and visually kind of looks like this kanji if you think about it.","ショウ","さかん","昌運 【ショウウン】 prosperity, fortune<br>昌泰 【ショウタイ】 Shoutai era (898.4.26-901.7.15)<br>隆昌 【リュウショウ】 prosperity",""],
