升:["丿: katakana no　廾: twenty; 2 hands","measuring box","SHO (1.8 liters)","It is a thousand or ten? I need my<strong> measuring box</strong>.","I can fit a thousand needles into my<strong> measuring box</strong>, but only if I bend the thousand.","ショウ","ます","升 【ショウ】 sho (unit of volume, approx. 1.8 litres)<br>升遷 【ショウセン】 rising up<br>一升 【イッショウ】 unit of old Japanese liquid measurement, 1800 cc","升 【ます】 measuring container, measure, box (seating at a theatre, etc.), square on a grid, cell of a grid, square bearing block (at the top of a pillar)<br>升売り 【ますうり】 selling something by the boxful (in a wooden masu box)<br>一升 【ひとます】 one square on a grid, one cell of a grid"],
昇:["日: day; sun　升: measuring box","rise up","ASCEND, rise in rank","This kanji does not mean \"get up\" or \"awake.\" It means rising, like the rising of a salary, or a promotion. STORY: You know that your salary has RISEN UP when your MEASURING BOX has enough dollar bills in it to reach the SUN.","We Measure the Sun to decide when we should<strong> Rise Up</strong> out of bed.","ショウ","のぼ.る","昇進 【ショウシン】 promotion, advancement, rising in rank<br>昇給 【ショウキュウ】 salary raise<br>上昇 【ジョウショウ】 rising, ascending, climbing<br>急上昇 【キュウジョウショウ】 sudden rise, steep climb, zoom","上る 【のぼる】 to ascend, to go up, to climb, to ascend (as a natural process, e.g. the sun), to rise, to go to (the capital), to be promoted, to add up to, to advance (in price), to swim up (a river), to sail up, to come up (on the agenda)"],
丸:["九: nine; baseball (RTK)　丶: dot; drop","round","ROUND","Nine plus a drop<strong> round</strong>s it off to ten!","Watch out for <a href=\"/study/kanji/%E5%A4%AA\">太</a> (<span class=\"frnr\">#126</span>). Here Heisig could have added a \"t\" and we would have had a much better keyword : <strong>rotund</strong>. <strong>Rotund</strong> is more specific than \"round\" which begs for confusion with <a href=\"/study/kanji/%E5%86%86\">円</a> (<span class=\"frnr\">#1952</span>). A dictionary search on \"fat\" or \"round\" doesn't yield this kanji, but \"rotund\" does! Primitive suggestion: the <em>Laughing Buddha</em> is often depicted as a <strong>rotund</strong>, smiling bald man in robes with a largely exposed pot belly stomach (symbolizing plenitude).","ガン","まる、 まる.める、 まる.い","丸 【ガン】 fishball, meatball, pill<br>丸薬 【ガンヤク】 pill<br>弾丸 【ダンガン】 bullet, shot, shell<br>砲丸 【ホウガン】 shell, shots, cannon ball","丸 【まる】 circle, entirety, whole, full, complete, money, dough, moola, enclosure inside a castle's walls, soft-shelled turtle, suffix for ship names, suffix for names of people (esp. infants), suffix for names of swords, armour, musical instruments, etc., suffix for names of dogs, horses, etc.<br>丸い 【まるい】 round, circular, spherical, harmonious, calm<br>日の丸 【ひのまる】 outline of the sun (esp. represented as a red circle), the Japanese flag<br>丸々 【まるまる】 plump, rotund, chubby, entirely, completely, wholly<br>丸める 【まるめる】 to make round, to roll up, to curl up, to seduce, to cajole, to explain away, to round off (a fraction), to lump together<br>丸い 【まるい】 round, circular, spherical, harmonious, calm<br>丸一日 【まるいちにち】 the whole day, all the day"],
寸:["寸: measurement; glue (RTK)","measurement","A BIT OF　SUN (3.03 cm)","The decimal system uses <em>drops</em> of <em>ten</em> as a<strong> measurement</strong>.","Use two lines (X axis and Y axis) to measure the dot (on the graph).","スン","","寸 【スン】 sun (approx. 3.03 cm)<br>寸法 【スンポウ】 measurement, size, extent, dimension, plan, intention, arrangement, schedule<br>一寸 【イッスン】 one sun (approx. 3.03 cm), a little bit (of time, distance, etc.)<br>原寸 【ゲンスン】 actual size, full size",""],
肘:["肉: meat; flesh (RTK) (月)　寸: measurement; glue (RTK)","elbow","ELBOW","Sometimes I get carried away and do<strong> elbow</strong> curls until the point where my forearm snaps off! When that happens I simply pull out the <em>glue</em> and re-attach the<strong> elbow</strong> to my <em>flesh</em>.","The<strong> elbow</strong> is the <em>flesh</em> that <em>glues</em> together the upper and lower arm.","チュウ","ひじ","肘関節 【チュウカンセツ】 elbow joint<br>肘頭滑液嚢炎 【チュウトウカツエキノウエン】 olecranoid bursitis, miner's elbow<br>掣肘 【セイチュウ】 restraint, restriction, control","肘 【ひじ】 elbow<br>肘掛け 【ひじかけ】 armrest (of a chair), elbow rest<br>両肘 【りょうひじ】 both elbows<br>テニス肘 【テニスひじ】 tennis elbow"],
専:["一: one; ceiling, floor (RTK)　由:reason　寸: measurement; glue (RTK)","specialty","EXCLUSIVELY, entirely","After you have chosen your <em>10</em> <em>fields</em> of study, <em>measure</em> how good you are at each to find out your<strong> specialty</strong>.","10 brains glued together allows you to specialize in any<strong> specialty</strong> that you want. Imagine each brain having its own<strong> specialty</strong>.","セン","もっぱ.ら","専 【セン】 having a fetish for ..., specializing in ..., majoring in ..., first, foremost, number one priority, doing as one pleases, acting selfishly, fired brick<br>専攻 【センコウ】 major subject, special study<br>住専 【ジュウセン】 housing-loan corporation<br>高専 【コウセン】 technical college, higher schools and colleges","専ら 【もっぱら】 wholly, solely, entirely, exclusively, devotedly, fixedly, principally, mostly, chiefly, mainly<br>専らにする 【もっぱらにする】 devote oneself to, to do as one pleases, to act selfishly"],
博:["十: ten; cross; needle (RTK)　尃: speciality","Dr.","EXTENSIVE (knowledge)　DOCTOR, Ph.D.","<em>Ten specialties</em> grants you the title of<strong> Dr.</strong> with a dot.","Watch for <a href=\"/study/kanji/%E5%8C%BB\">医</a> (<span class=\"frnr\">#1694</span>), the sooner the better! In fact this kanji refers to someone well \"learned\", with extensive knowledge. This could apply to any kind of field. The kanji 医 (\"doctor\") is directly related to medicine. I would suggest to take away completely the idea of medicine here, and use a popular character whose name includes the keyword such as \"Dr. Who\", \"Dr. Jekyll\", even \"Dr. Dobb's\" if you're into programming.","ハク、 バク","","博 【ハク】 doctor, PhD, exposition, fair, exhibition<br>博物館 【ハクブツカン】 museum<br>文博 【ブンハク】 doctor of literature<br>医博 【イハク】 doctor of medicine<br>博 【ハク】 doctor, PhD, exposition, fair, exhibition<br>博奕 【バクエキ】 gambling<br>賭博 【トバク】 gambling",""],
