辺:["刀: sword; dagger, saber (RTK) (刂)　辶: walk; road; way (RTK)","environs","VICINITY, side　BORDERLAND, outer regions","Caution: this kanji doesn't mean environment; it means \"environs; boundary; border; vicinity\". To separate the<strong> environs</strong>, create the border by placing <em>daggers</em> on the <em>road</em>.","To protect the<strong> environs</strong> around their village, samurai would travel the <em>road</em>s with their <em>swords</em>.","ヘン","あた.り、 ほと.り、 -べ","辺 【ヘン】 area, vicinity, region, side (of triangle, rectangle, etc.), circumstances<br>辺境 【ヘンキョウ】 remote region, frontier (district), border(land)<br>周辺 【シュウヘン】 circumference, outskirts, environs, around, in the area of, in the vicinity of, (computer) peripheral<br>海辺 【ウミベ】 beach, seashore, seaside, coast","辺り 【あたり】 on the bank of, by the side of (e.g. a river, pond), (in the) neighbourhood, neighborhood, vicinity, nearby, around (Sunday, last year, etc...), for instance<br>辺り一面 【あたりいちめん】 all around, as far as the eye can see<br>何処ら辺り 【どこらあたり】 where, whereabouts<br>御辺 【ごへん】 you (usu. used by samurai to their equals or people of slightly higher standing)<br>辺り 【あたり】 on the bank of, by the side of (e.g. a river, pond), (in the) neighbourhood, neighborhood, vicinity, nearby, around (Sunday, last year, etc...), for instance<br>片辺 【かたほとり】 corner, remote country place"],
