輸:["車: car　亼: assemble; meeting　刖: butcher","transport","TRANSPORT","The <em>car</em> is a cattle-car, used to<strong> transport</strong> animals for the <em>butcher</em>'s <em>meeting</em> - a convention on new butchering techniques. Hear the screams of the animals as it pulls up in front of the convention hall, where the butchers are waiting with their knives out front.","The vehicle<strong> transport</strong>s animals for a meeting with the butcher.","ユ、 シュ","","輸入 【ユニュウ】 importation, import, introduction, afferent<br>輸出 【ユシュツ】 export, efferent<br>運輸 【ウンユ】 transportation<br>密輸 【ミツユ】 smuggling, contraband trade<br>輸入 【ユニュウ】 importation, import, introduction, afferent<br>輸出 【ユシュツ】 export, efferent",""],
喩:["口: mouth　兪: steal","metaphor","LIKEN","<strong>Metaphor</strong>ically speaking, all the equipment in your <em>mouth</em> is basically just a <em>meeting of butchers</em>, designed to pulverize whatever meat you put in there.","<strong>Metaphor</strong>: A good <strong>metaphor</strong> flows from the <em>mouth</em> like the <em>meeting of flesh and saber</em>, smoothly piercing the listener with its meaning. But a bad <strong>metaphor</strong> is like when you barely nick the <em>flesh</em> and only spill <em>two drops</em> of blood or when your <em>saber</em> doesn't penetrate at all but rather bends into a くく shape when you whack the <em>flesh</em>. (Note: This story incorporates both the traditional form of the kanji (口＋兪) and the simplified form (口＋俞)) .","ユ","たと.える、 さと.す","隠喩 【インユ】 metaphor<br>教諭 【キョウユ】 (licensed) teacher","例える 【たとえる】 to compare, to liken, to speak figuratively, to illustrate, to use a simile"],
