冗:["冖: crown 　几: table; wind (RTK)","superfluous","REDUNDANT, superfluous","The king's crown was blown off by the wind. \"Oh well,\" he said, \"it's just a<strong> superfluous</strong> symbol.\"","The court jester wears a <em>crown</em> and is full of <em>wind</em> with bad jokes. He is<strong> superfluous</strong> to the King's court. This kanji is read as \"JOU\" and commonly used to create the compound for <em>jou-dan</em> 冗談 (jest or joke) hence court jester. Also <em>jou-go</em> 冗語 (redundancy) and <em>jou-in</em> 冗員 (useless workers) 員-<a href=\"/study/kanji/%E5%93%A1\">員</a> (<span class=\"frnr\">#59</span>).","ジョウ","","冗 【ジョウ】 uselessness<br>冗談 【ジョウダン】 jest, joke, funny story",""],
冥:["冖: crown 　日: day; sun　六: six","Hades","DARK","The beast of <strong>hades</strong> one <em>day</em> will wear a <em>crown</em>, and the number of the beast is <em>666</em>.","In<strong> Hades</strong> you have to work <em>six days</em> a week before <em>crowning</em> it with something vaguely resembling a weekend. Oh wait, that's Japan.","メイ、 ミョウ","くら.い","瞑想 【メイソウ】 meditation, contemplation<br>冥界 【メイカイ】 hades, realm of the dead<br>晦冥 【カイメイ】 darkness<br>天地晦冥 【テンチカイメイ】 The world is covered in darkness, All is plunged into darkness<br>冥福 【メイフク】 happiness in the next world<br>冥利 【ミョウリ】 providence, luck, favor, favour, advantage","暗い 【くらい】 dark, gloomy, dark (in colour), dull, depressed, dispirited, sorrowful, bitter (as in a dark past), unclear, unfamiliar, unknown"],
軍:["冖: crown 　車: car","army","ARMY, military","British <strong>army</strong> <em>cars</em> are at the service of the <em>crown</em>.","Imagine a <em>crown</em> is the hood ornament on every<strong> army</strong> <em>car</em>.","グン","いくさ","軍 【グン】 army, force, troops<br>軍隊 【グンタイ】 armed forces, military, troops<br>将軍 【ショウグン】 general, shogun<br>海軍 【カイグン】 navy","戦 【いくさ】 war, battle, campaign, fight, troops, forces<br>軍神 【ぐんしん】 god of war, war hero<br>海兵遠征軍 【かいへいえんせいいくさ】 Marine Expeditionary Force (US)<br>船軍 【ふないくさ】 naval battle, navy"],
輝:["光: ray; light　軍: army; chariot (RTK)","radiance","SHINE BRILLIANTLY","Rays of light emitted from Apollo's chariot =<strong> radiance</strong>. Don't put the sun into this kanji. The rays are coming from the chariot directly!","<strong>Radiance</strong> is an army of rays.","キ","かがや.く","輝度 【キド】 brightness, clearness, luminance<br>輝安鉱 【キアンコウ】 stibnite (mineral), antimonite<br>光輝 【コウキ】 brightness, splendour, splendor<br>輝輝 【キキ】 brilliance","輝く 【かがやく】 to shine, to glitter, to sparkle<br>輝くばかり 【かがやくばかり】 radiant"],
運:["軍: army; chariot (RTK)　辶: walk; road; way (RTK)","carry","CARRY, transport　MOVE　FORTUNE, fate","Don’t confuse it with “take along” (287). In that one, there was a car so you could take along your friends once you found them on the road. In this one, there is an army chariot just to<strong> carry</strong> military supplies (sorry no room for you).","Roads<strong> carry</strong> armies (in contrast to seas<strong> carry</strong>ing navies or skies<strong> carry</strong>ing air forces).","ウン","はこ.ぶ","運 【ウン】 fortune, luck<br>運転手 【ウンテンシュ】 driver, chauffeur<br>幸運 【コウウン】 good luck, fortune<br>不運 【フウン】 misfortune, bad luck, ill luck, ill fortune, bad break, tough luck, mischance","運ぶ 【はこぶ】 to carry, to transport, to move, to convey, to come, to go, to wield (a tool, etc.), to use, to go (well, etc.), to proceed, to progress"],
冠:["冖: crown 　元: beginning; origin","crown","CROWN","Remember the SUPERFLUOUS<strong> CROWN</strong> that flew away in the WIND? Well now the king is saying \"i should have had the thing GLUED to my head from the BEGINNING\".","A <strong>crown</strong>, from the <em>beginning</em> of the new king's life, is <em>glued</em> to him. He must inherit it.","カン","かんむり","冠 【カンムリ】 cap (esp. a traditional cap worn with sokutai or ikan clothing), crown, diadem, coronet, top kanji radical, first verse of a haikai, etc., best, peerless, first<br>冠水 【カンスイ】 being covered with water (i.e. in a flood), being submerged, being inundated, flooding<br>栄冠 【エイカン】 laurels, garland<br>王冠 【オウカン】 crown, diadem, bottle cap","冠 【かんむり】 cap (esp. a traditional cap worn with sokutai or ikan clothing), crown, diadem, coronet, top kanji radical, first verse of a haikai, etc., best, peerless, first<br>冠海雀 【かんむりうみすずめ】 Japanese murrelet (Synthliboramphus wumizusume), crested murrelet<br>お冠 【おかんむり】 bad temper, bad mood<br>初冠 【ういこうぶり】 crowning a boy for the first time at a coming-of-age ceremony, noh cap with a rolled or drooping tail (indicative of nobility)"],
