坑:["土: ground; land; soil　亢: high spirits; whirlwind (RTK)","pit","PIT (of a mine)","A <em>whirlwind</em> digs a hole in the ground throwing out lots of <em>dirt</em> until it ends up with a giant <strong>pit</strong>.","Tazmanian Devil whirlwinds a<strong> pit</strong> into the soil. Note: Take care difference between<strong> pit</strong> and rut.","コウ","","坑 【コウ】 pit (esp. of a mine)<br>坑口 【コウコウ】 pithead, minehead<br>炭鉱 【タンコウ】 coal mine, coal pit<br>金坑 【キンコウ】 gold mine",""],
高:["亠: roof; hat (RTK)　口: mouth　冂: hood; belt (RTK)　口: mouth","tall","HIGH, tall; expensive　AMOUNT, quantity","Two little aliens in a trenchcoat and <em>top hat</em>, trying to look<strong> TALL</strong>. The bottom one, in the glass helmet, is under the coat. The top one has his top hat pulled down in disguise, so all you can see is his mouth.","Here we have TWO MOUTHS each wearing a different hat. The top one is wearing a TOP HAT which is know to be as a<strong> TALL</strong> hat. The bottom one is wearing a SPACE HELMET which is known as an EXPENSIVE hat. (this kanji means both).","コウ","たか.い、 たか、 -だか、 たか.まる、 たか.める","高 【コウ】 high school, high-<br>高校 【コウコウ】 senior high school, high school<br>最高 【サイコウ】 highest, supreme, the most<br>標高 【ヒョウコウ】 elevation, height above sea level","高い 【たかい】 high, tall, expensive<br>高鼾 【たかいびき】 loud snoring<br>高 【たか】 quantity, amount, volume, number, amount of money<br>高い 【たかい】 high, tall, expensive<br>威高 【いたか】 arrogant<br>背高 【せいたか】 tallness, tall person<br>高まる 【たかまる】 to rise, to swell, to be promoted<br>高める 【たかめる】 to raise, to lift, to boost, to enhance"],
享:["亠: roof; hat (RTK)　口: mouth　子: child","receive","ENJOY, receive","In basketball however, tall children<strong> receive</strong> all the attention.","<em>Tall children</em><strong> receive</strong> all the attention. They also make great<strong> receive</strong>rs in football... this kanji also means 'catch' (therefore a football<strong> receive</strong>r is a great image).","キョウ、 コウ","う.ける","享受 【キョウジュ】 reception, acceptance, enjoyment, being given<br>饗宴 【キョウエン】 feast, banquet<br>永享 【エイキョウ】 Eikyou era (1429.9.5-1441.2.17)<br>貞享 【ジョウキョウ】 Joukyou era (1684.2.21-1688.9.30)","受ける 【うける】 to receive, to get, to catch (e.g. a ball), to be struck by (wind, waves, sunlight, etc.), to sustain (damage), to incur (a loss), to suffer (an injury), to feel (influence), to undergo (e.g. surgery), to take (a test), to accept (a challenge), to be given (e.g. life, talent), to follow, to succeed, to be descended from, to face (south, etc.), to be modified by, to obtain (a pawned item, etc.) by paying a fee, to be well-received, to become popular, to go down well"],
