周:["冂: hood; belt (RTK)　吉: good luck; lidded crock (RTK); aerosol can (RTK)","circumference","PERIPHERY, around; cycle","If my LIDDED CROCK has the same<strong> CIRCUMFERENCE</strong> as my head, I like to use it as a HELMET.","When the <em>ground</em> has an <em>opening</em> (a hole), you need to cover the entire<strong> circumference</strong> or you will fall in.","シュウ","まわ.り","周 【シュウ】 Zhou (dynasty of China), Chou, perimeter, counter for laps or circuits<br>周囲 【シュウイ】 surroundings, environs, circumference<br>一周 【イッシュウ】 once around, a revolution, a lap, a turn, a round, one full year<br>円周 【エンシュウ】 circumference","周り 【まわり】 circumference, girth, surroundings, neighbourhood, neighborhood, vicinity<br>周りの人 【まわりのひと】 surrounding people"],
週:["周: circumference; lap　辶: walk; road; way (RTK)","week","WEEK","Imagine a road built so well that it takes only a<strong> week</strong> to travel the circumference of the earth.","Actually the<strong> week</strong> is like a never ending <em>road</em> where we travel in a circle through the same seven days again and again, the <em>circumference</em> is always the same. <a href=\"/study/kanji/%E5%91%A8\">周</a> (<span class=\"frnr\">#317</span>) also means circuit or lap, so that also makes think about the rotations of the moon, sun and the earth -- all important for measuring all kinds of time periods.","シュウ","","週 【シュウ】 week<br>週間 【シュウカン】 week, weekly<br>来週 【ライシュウ】 next week<br>先週 【センシュウ】 last week, the week before",""],
