敗:["貝: shellfish; money, clam (RTK)　攵: strike; taskmaster (RTK)","failure","BE DEFEATED","The <em>shell</em> who was defeated before (<a href=\"/study/kanji/%E8%B2%A0\">負</a> (<span class=\"frnr\">#63</span>)) is being chastised by the <em>taskmaster</em> for his<strong> failure</strong> to win.","If you end up in<strong> failure</strong>, you give money to the taskmaster to train you.","ハイ","やぶ.れる","敗 【ハイ】 loss, defeat, counter for losses<br>敗戦 【ハイセン】 defeat, losing a war<br>勝敗 【ショウハイ】 victory or defeat, issue (of battle), outcome<br>腐敗 【フハイ】 decomposition, putrefaction, putrescence, spoilage, corruption, degeneracy, decay, depravity","敗れる 【やぶれる】 to be defeated, to be beaten, to be unsuccessful, to lose"],
枚:["木: tree; wood　攵: strike; taskmaster (RTK)","a sheet of","COUNTER FOR FLAT THINGS","The <em>taskmaster</em> is a strict bathroom monitor who hands out only one sheet of really rough, splintery toilet paper per person. You can see the <em>wood</em> fibers.","This <em>taskmaster</em> is the bathroom nazi: he counts how many <strong>sheets of</strong> toilet paper and tissue you use, and then tells you what % of a tree you just killed.","マイ、 バイ","","枚 【マイ】 counter for flat objects (e.g. sheets of paper)<br>枚数 【マイスウ】 the number of flat things, win-loss difference which influences the ranking of wrestlers<br>一枚 【イチマイ】 one thin flat object, one sheet<br>二枚 【ニマイ】 two sheets (pieces) (of paper)<br>枚を銜む 【バイヲフクム】 (of a horse) to be gagged",""],
故:["古: old　攵: strike; taskmaster (RTK)","happenstance","OLD; the late　INCIDENT　REASON, cause","An <em>OLD TASKMASTER</em> is no<strong> happenstance</strong> (coincidence). The older you get the more rigid in your ways.","Need to disambiguate from <a href=\"/study/kanji/%E6%95%B5\">敵</a> (<span class=\"frnr\">#475</span>) as it's easy to mix up <strong>antique</strong> and <strong>old</strong> here. Let's think of an accidental president -- he is an <strong>old</strong> <strong>taskmaster</strong> who has managed to win the election by<strong> happenstance</strong> .","コ","ゆえ、 ふる.い、 もと","故 【コ】 the late (deceased)<br>故障 【コショウ】 breakdown, failure, fault, accident, out of order, damage, hurt, objection, protest<br>事故 【ジコ】 accident, incident, trouble, circumstances, reasons<br>交通事故 【コウツウジコ】 traffic accident","故 【ゆえ】 reason, cause, circumstances<br>故に 【ゆえに】 therefore, consequently<br>何故 【なぜ】 why, how<br>事故 【じこ】 accident, incident, trouble, circumstances, reasons<br>古い 【ふるい】 old (not person), aged, ancient, antiquated, stale, threadbare, outmoded, obsolete article<br>元 【もと】 former, ex-"],
