幅:["巾: towel　畐: to fill; wealth (RTK)","hanging scroll","WIDTH, range","In the west, the rich use $100 bills to light their cigars... In Japan, after showering, when the wealthy don't have any clean towels, they simply grab a<strong> hanging scroll</strong> off the wall and use it to dry off!","The towels of the wealthy:<strong> hanging scroll</strong>s.","フク","はば","幅 【フク】 scroll, counter for scrolls<br>幅員 【フクイン】 breadth, extent<br>増幅 【ゾウフク】 amplification (elec.), magnification, amplification, making larger<br>双幅 【ソウフク】 pair of hanging scrolls","幅 【はば】 width, breadth, freedom (e.g. of thought), latitude, gap, difference (e.g. in price), range (e.g. of voice)<br>幅広い 【はばひろい】 extensive, wide, broad<br>大幅 【おおはば】 big, large, drastic, substantial, full-width cloth (approx. 72 cm wide for traditional Japanese clothing; approx. 140 cm wide for Western clothing)<br>肩幅 【かたはば】 shoulder width (breadth)"],
帽:["巾: towel　冒: risk","cap","HEADGEAR","If you wear a towel as a<strong> cap</strong>, you are at risk of being seized and searched in U.S. airports.","Originally the first<strong> cap</strong> was a turban which was a <em>towel</em> wrapped around the head to keep the <em>sun</em> out of the <em>eyes</em>.","ボウ、 モウ","ずきん、 おお.う","帽 【ボウ】 hat, cap<br>帽子 【ボウシ】 hat, cap<br>脱帽 【ダツボウ】 removing one's hat, admiring someone greatly, \"taking off one's hat\" to someone<br>赤帽 【アカボウ】 redcap, porter",""],
幕:["莫: must not; graveyard (RTK)　巾: towel","curtain","CURTAIN, tent　SHOGUNATE","There is a <em>graveyard</em> outside my house that scares me, so I put a huge towel over the window to serve as a<strong> curtain</strong> so I can get a good nights sleep.","When you're dead in the <em>graveyard</em>, \"it's <strong>curtains</strong> for you.\"","マク、 バク","とばり","幕 【マク】 curtain, bunting, act (in play)<br>幕切れ 【マクギレ】 fall of the curtain, last scene, end of act<br>黒幕 【クロマク】 black curtain, wire puller, mastermind, political fixer, power broker<br>内幕 【ウチマク】 lowdown, inside curtain, inside information, hidden circumstances, inside facts, inner workings, undisclosed circumstances<br>幕府 【バクフ】 bakufu, shogunate<br>幕末 【バクマツ】 closing days of the Tokugawa shogunate, end of Edo era<br>帷幕 【イバク】 curtain, field staff headquarters, secret meeting place<br>倒幕 【トウバク】 overthrow of the shogunate",""],
幌:["巾: towel　日: day; sun　光: ray; light","canopy","AWNING, hood","A<strong> canopy</strong> is a <em>towel</em> to block the <em>suns</em> <em>ray</em>s.","From the <em>Hitch-Hiker's Guide to the Universe</em>: A towel is useful, among other things, as a<strong> canopy</strong> to keep out the sun's rays from your face while napping.","コウ","ほろ、 とばり","","幌 【ほろ】 canopy (esp. the cloth or canvas used for it), awning, top (of a convertible), hood, helmet cape, cloth covering one's back to protect against arrows during battle<br>幌蚊帳 【ほろがや】 tent-shaped mosquito net (often used to protect infants)<br>帳 【とばり】 curtain, hanging, bunting"],
錦:["金: gold; metal　白: white　巾: towel","brocade","BROCADE","<strong>Brocade</strong> is the art of sewing <em>gold</em> on a <em>white towel</em>.","Never heard of this word before encountering it here. So it turns out that the fanciest<strong> brocade</strong> in the world is actually a towel used by a Turkish monarch. It's embroidered with <em>gold</em> and <em>cocaine</em>. Yes, <em>cocaine</em> - what you thought it'd be something else? That is some true art right there. I think a great many people would want to own this towel.","キン","にしき","錦華鳥 【キンカチョウ】 zebra finch (Taeniopygia guttata)<br>錦旗 【キンキ】 pennant, gold-brocade flag<br>蜀錦 【ショッキン】 type of brocade","錦 【にしき】 brocade, fine dress, fine clothes<br>錦絵 【にしきえ】 colour (woodblock) print, color print<br>蜀江の錦 【しょっこうのにしき】 type of red brocade originally from the ancient Chinese country of Shu and passed on in Japan, type of brocade made in Sichuan during the Ming period<br>綾錦 【あやにしき】 twill damask and brocade"],
