柿:["木: tree; wood　市: market; city; town","persimmon","PERSIMMON","Nobody buys<strong> persimmon</strong>s at the <em>market</em>, because there's a <em>tree</em> in the middle where you can pick them for free.","<strong>Persimmon</strong> = かき - they grow on <em>trees</em> and are sold at the <em>market</em>.","シ","かき","熟柿 【ジュクシ】 ripe persimmon","柿 【かき】 kaki, Japanese persimmon (Diospyros kaki)<br>柿の木 【かきのき】 (Japanese) persimmon tree (Diospyros kaki)<br>筆柿 【ふでがき】 fudegaki (variety of sweet Japanese persimmon)<br>ピー柿 【ピーかき】 mix of peanuts and spicy baked or fried mochi chips in the shape of kaki (Japanese persimmon) seeds"],
