風:["几: table; wind (RTK)　丿: katakana no　虫: insect","wind","WIND　MANNER","They say that when an INSECT flaps its wings even the single DROP of<strong> WIND</strong> that it creates is sometimes enough to create a hurricane on the other side of the Earth.","The<strong> WIND</strong> usually carries things around in it - <em>drops</em> of rain or snow, and lots of <em>insects</em>.","フウ、 フ","かぜ、 かざ-、 -かぜ","風 【フウ】 method, manner, way, style, appearance, air, tendency, folk song (genre of the Shi Jing), wind (one of the five elements)<br>風邪 【カゼ】 common cold, cold, influenza, flu, ague<br>台風 【タイフウ】 typhoon, hurricane<br>暴風 【ボウフウ】 storm, windstorm, gale<br>振り 【フリ】 swing, shake, wave, swinging, appearance, behaviour, pretence (pretense), show, pretending (to), going to restaurant, hotel etc. without a reservation or introduction, move (dance), postures, lead in (e.g. to a running joke, asking a question), lead up, unsewn part of a hanging sleeve on a traditional Japanese woman's garment, counter for swords, blades, etc.<br>風 【フウ】 method, manner, way, style, appearance, air, tendency, folk song (genre of the Shi Jing), wind (one of the five elements)<br>中風 【チュウフウ】 palsy, paralysis<br>破風 【ハフ】 gable","風 【かぜ】 wind, breeze, draught, draft, manner, behaviour, behavior, cold, influenza<br>風邪 【かぜ】 common cold, cold, influenza, flu, ague<br>旋風 【せんぷう】 whirlwind, commotion, sensation, hullabaloo<br>追い風 【おいかぜ】 tailwind, fair wind, favorable wind (favourable), favorable condition (favourable), advantageous situation"],
