豚:["月: moon; month　豕: pig; sow (RTK)","pork","PIG","<strong>Pork</strong> comes from the flesh of a sow.","One possible pictograph for \"<strong>sow</strong>\" primitive: the top line is a feeding trough, the stroke touching it is the head, the long curved stroke is the body (with a little hook at the end for the curly tail), and the four remaining strokes are the sow's legs.","トン","ぶた","豚 【トン】 pig, pork<br>豚肉 【ブタニク】 pork<br>河豚 【フグ】 puffer fish, blow fish, fugu, globefish, swellfish<br>養豚 【ヨウトン】 pig-keeping, pig farming","豚 【ぶた】 pig (Sus scrofa domesticus), fat person<br>豚肉 【ぶたにく】 pork<br>子豚 【こぶた】 piglet<br>萌え豚 【もえぶた】 anime freak, person overly interested in female anime and video game characters"],
逐:["豕: pig; sow (RTK)　辶: walk; road; way (RTK)","pursue","DRIVE OUT　ONE BY ONE","In association with <a href=\"/study/kanji/%E9%81%82\">遂</a> (<span class=\"frnr\">#579</span>), our <em>sow</em> is on the road <strong>pursuing</strong> a mate.","The <em>pig</em> is on the <em>road</em> in the<strong> pursue</strong> of the turtle who is trying to <a href=\"/study/kanji/%E9%80%83\">逃</a> (<span class=\"frnr\">#301</span>). (See story on <a href=\"/study/kanji/%E9%80%83\">逃</a> (<span class=\"frnr\">#301</span>) &amp; <a href=\"/study/kanji/%E9%81%82\">遂</a> (<span class=\"frnr\">#579</span>)).","チク","","逐一 【チクイチ】 one by one, in detail, minutely<br>逐語的 【チクゴテキ】 word-for-word, verbatim<br>駆逐 【クチク】 extermination, expulsion, destruction<br>放逐 【ホウチク】 expulsion, ejection, dismissal, ostracism",""],
遂:["丷: animal horns (RTK)　豕: pig; sow (RTK)　辶: walk; road; way (RTK)","consummate","ACCOMPLISH, carry out","This is still Miss Piggy only she's gotten <em>horny</em> (as she often does) and now she's <em>pursuing</em> Kermit to help her<strong> consummate</strong> her desires.","I don't often complain about Heisig's keywords - but 'consummate' is a little misleading. Think about this kanji in terms of <strong>ACCOMPLISH</strong> or \"realize\" rather than a sexual encounter. Or, combine the two: the policemen thought they had <strong>accomplished</strong> the task of <em>driving out</em> (see <strong>pursue</strong>, last frame) all the <em>sows</em>, but they received a phone call reporting two <em>horny</em> pigs <strong>CONSUMMATING</strong> on a <em>road</em>. When they got there, they found a male and female police officer, not pigs!","スイ","と.げる、 つい.に","遂行 【スイコウ】 accomplishment, execution<br>未遂 【ミスイ】 attempt (e.g. at crime)<br>自殺未遂 【ジサツミスイ】 attempted suicide","遂げる 【とげる】 to accomplish, to achieve, to carry out, to arrive at (a certain outcome), to come to, to end with<br>遂に 【ついに】 finally, at last, in the end"],
家:["宀: house (RTK)　豕: pig; sow (RTK)","house","HOUSE, home　FAMILY, House","Think of \"The Three Little Pigs\". There was a <em>house</em> made of straw, another made of sticks, and a third made of bricks, each occupied by a <em>pig</em>. So, naturally, <em>housetop</em> over <em>pig</em> means<strong> house</strong>, the central element of that story.","Man, ever hear of cleaning? This<strong> house</strong> is a <em>pig</em> sty.","カ、 ケ","いえ、 や、 うち","家 【カ】 -ist (used after a noun indicating someone's occupation, pursuits, disposition, etc.), -er<br>家族 【カゾク】 family, members of a family<br>作家 【サッカ】 author, writer, novelist, artist<br>画家 【ガカ】 painter, artist<br>家 【ケ】 house (e.g. of Tokugawa), family<br>家来 【ケライ】 retainer, retinue, servant<br>一家 【イッカ】 a house, a home, a family, a household, one's family, one's folks, a style<br>両家 【リョウケ】 both families","家 【いえ】 house, residence, dwelling, family, household, lineage, family name<br>家主 【やぬし】 landlord, landlady, house owner, home owner, head of the household<br>貸家 【かしや】 house for rent<br>我が家 【わがや】 one's house, one's home, one's family<br>屋 【や】 (something) shop, somebody who sells (something) or works as (something), somebody with a (certain) personality trait, house, roof<br>家内 【かない】 (my) wife, inside the home, one's family<br>大屋 【おおや】 landlord, landlady<br>貸家 【かしや】 house for rent<br>家 【うち】 house, home (one's own), (one's) family, (one's) household<br>家中 【うちじゅう】 whole family, all (members of) family, all over the house<br>御内 【おうち】 home, your home, your group, their home"],
