国:["囗: box; pent in (RTK)　玉: jewel; ball","country","COUNTRY","In my<strong> country</strong> (England) the crown <em>jewels</em> are kept <em>pent-in</em> in the Tower of London. Which happens to be where enemies of the state were once also <em>pent-in</em> (probably for trying to steal those <em>jewels</em>).","Just think of Japan, a<strong> country</strong> which is like a jewel but historically very enclosed.","コク","くに","国民 【コクミン】 nation, nationality, people, citizen<br>国語 【コクゴ】 national language, Japanese language (often as a school subject in Japan), native Japanese words (as opposed to loanwords)<br>外国 【ガイコク】 foreign country<br>全国 【ゼンコク】 countrywide, nationwide, whole country, national","国 【くに】 country, state, region, national government, central government, home (i.e. hometown, home country), province (of Japan), land, earth<br>国境 【こっきょう】 national border, provincial border<br>我が国 【わがくに】 our country, our land, one's own country<br>唐国 【からくに】 China, Korea"],
団:["囗: box; pent in (RTK)　寸: measurement; glue (RTK)","group","COLLECTIVE, group, organization","When you are admitted into a<strong> group</strong> like the Yakuza, you're well and truly done (だん) for. You must stick to the<strong> group</strong> like <em>glue</em>, and you will be <em>pent-in</em> for life, never being able to leave.","A <em>pent-in</em><strong> group</strong> will naturally be more cohesive, or \"<em>glued</em> together.\"","ダン、 トン","かたまり、 まる.い","団 【ダン】 body, group, party, company, troupe<br>団体 【ダンタイ】 organization, organisation, association<br>集団 【シュウダン】 group, mass<br>劇団 【ゲキダン】 troupe, theatrical company<br>布団 【フトン】 futon (quilted Japanese-style mattress laid out on the floor), round cushion used for Zen meditation (traditionally made of woven bulrush leaves)<br>座布団 【ザブトン】 zabuton (flat floor cushion used when sitting or kneeling; usu. rectangular)",""],
因:["囗: box; pent in (RTK)　大: large; St Bernard (RTK)","cause","CAUSE","We once had a <em>dog</em> with big paws // and oh what great trouble he'd<strong> cause</strong> // we built a huge pen // to keep him <em>pent in</em> // and stop him from breaking more laws //.","Why is there poop on the kitchen floor? Oh, the<strong> cause</strong> is that you kept the <em>dog</em> <em>pent in</em> the house all day. Next time remember to walk him.","イン","よ.る、 ちな.む","因 【イン】 cause, factor, hetu (direct cause, esp. as opposed to indirect conditions), the basis of one's argument (in hetuvidya)<br>因縁 【インネン】 fate, destiny, connection, tie, bond, origin, pretext, justification, hetu and prataya (direct causes and indirect conditions, which underlie the actions of all things)<br>原因 【ゲンイン】 cause, origin, source<br>要因 【ヨウイン】 main cause, primary factor","因る 【よる】 to be due to, to be caused by, to depend on, to turn on, to be based on, to come from<br>因む 【ちなむ】 to be associated (with), to be connected (with)"],
