悼:["心: heart; mind (忄; ⺗)　卓: eminent","lament","MOURN","When Dumbledore died, everyone<strong> lament</strong>ed it greatly. He was buried with his <em>sunflower wand</em> in his hand as he was so <em>eminent</em>. Even the death-eaters were <em>imperiused</em> to make them look like they were<strong> lament</strong>ing his death.","Closely related to grief, mourning and regret, it was difficult for me to isolate this kanji. A<strong> lament</strong> is a song or poem that deals with loss or regret. This brings to mind the works of the world's most <em>eminent</em> artists, their brilliance and powerful works owed to their <em>emotional states of mind</em>.","トウ","いた.む","悼辞 【トウジ】 funeral address, message of condolence, words of condolence<br>哀悼 【アイトウ】 condolence, regret, tribute, sorrow, sympathy, lament<br>追悼 【ツイトウ】 mourning (dead persons), memorial","悼む 【いたむ】 to grieve over, to mourn, to lament"],
