采:["爪: claw; vulture (RTK)　木: tree; wood","grab","GATHER","You ever wondered why this appeared as a primitive in so many RTK1 kanji? Well, you should know that once a vulture<strong> grab</strong>s hold of a <em>tree</em>, he can never let go. Even Heisig couldn't shake him loose.","A common meaning for this kanji is 'DICE'. --- Ever wonder what <em>vultures</em> do up in the <em>trees</em>? They play DICE. But of course, being vultures, they are always <strong>grabbing</strong> the dice away from each other.","サイ","と.る、 いろどり","采 【サイ】 dice, die, baton (of command)<br>さいの目 【サイノメ】 pip (spot on a die), small cube (esp. of food), die, dice<br>喝采 【カッサイ】 acclamation, applause, ovation, cheers<br>拍手喝采 【ハクシュカッサイ】 clapping and cheering, applause",""],
