径:["彳: going, act; line; column (RTK)　圣: holy; spool (RTK)","diameter","PATH　DIAMETER","Scientists recently measured the<strong> diameter</strong> of Earth by drilling a deep hole and dropping a <em>line</em> of thread off a humongous <em>spool</em> until it got to the other side.","Suggestion: Replace \"spool\" with \"toilet paper/roll\". Reasons: (1) <em>Toilet paper/roll</em> usually comes on a <em>spool</em>. (2) <em>Toilet paper</em> is used to clean the <em>soil</em> off your <em>crotch</em>. Story: Measure the<strong> diameter</strong> of a <em>column</em> (maybe Nelson's Column in London?) using a roll of <em>toilet paper</em>. Spool also appears in <a href=\"/study/kanji/%E8%8C%8E\">茎</a> (<span class=\"frnr\">#772</span>), <a href=\"/study/kanji/%E6%80%AA\">怪</a> (<span class=\"frnr\">#773</span>), <a href=\"/study/kanji/%E8%BB%BD\">軽</a> (<span class=\"frnr\">#774</span>), <a href=\"/study/kanji/%E7%B5%8C\">経</a> (<span class=\"frnr\">#1460</span>).","ケイ","みち、 こみち、 さしわたし、 ただちに","径 【ケイ】 diameter<br>経路 【ケイロ】 course, route, path, channel, process, means<br>直径 【チョッケイ】 diameter<br>小道 【コミチ】 path, lane, small diameter, small radius","道 【みち】 road, street, way, path, course, route, lane, distance, ways (e.g. \"a long ways\"), the way (of proper conduct, etc.), one's way, morals, teachings (esp. Confucian or Buddhist), dogma, field (of medicine, etc.), subject, way, method, means<br>小道 【こみち】 path, lane, small diameter, small radius"],
