柄:["木: tree; wood　丙: 3rd","design","CHARACTER　STATUS　HANDLE, grip; shaft","Half Way!!!!","This is a \"<em>design</em>\" as in a \"pattern\", not a verb as in \"to <em>design</em>\". The <strong>tree</strong> grain <em>design</em> was too expensive for the <strong>third class</strong> airline to use for the panelling. They just painted it.","ヘイ","がら、 え、 つか","横柄 【オウヘイ】 arrogance, haughtiness, insolence<br>小柄 【ショウヘイ】 sterigma","柄 【がら】 pattern, design, body build, figure, physique, essential qualities, character, nature, appropriate to, fitting of, suitable for<br>柄にも無い 【がらにもない】 out of character, unlike one<br>事柄 【ことがら】 matter, thing, affair, circumstance<br>人柄 【ひとがら】 personality, character, personal appearance, gentility<br>柄 【え】 handle, grip, stalk (of a mushroom, leaf, etc.)<br>柄鏡 【えかがみ】 traditional mirror with a handle, popular since the Muromachi period<br>取り柄 【とりえ】 worth, redeeming feature, merit, gain, profit<br>長柄 【ながえ】 long handle, long-handled spear, long shaft<br>柄 【つか】 hilt (of a sword), haft (of a dagger), handgrip<br>柄頭 【つかがしら】 pommel<br>鎌柄 【かまつか】 sickle handle, goby minnow (Pseudogobio esocinus), Oriental photinia (species of shrub, Photinia villosa), Asiatic dayflower (Commelina communis), Joseph's-coat (species of amaranth, Amaranthus tricolor)"],
