挫:["手: hand; fingers (扌) (RTK)　坐: sit","sprain","BREAK, sprain","I <strong>sprained</strong> my <em>fingers</em> when I <em>sat in meditation</em> (by sitting in a strange position).","(Using the primitives in the RTK1 addendum) The workers at the <em>assembly line</em> in the coal cave (<a href=\"/study/kanji/%E5%BA%A7\">座</a> (<span class=\"frnr\">#1100</span>)) frequently claim to \"<strong>sprain</strong>\" their <em>fingers</em> because working within all the <em>dirt</em> around them is hard and they'd much rather stay at home.","ザ、 サ","くじ.く、 くじ.ける","挫折 【ザセツ】 setback, failure (e.g. plans, business), frustration, discouragement<br>挫傷 【ザショウ】 bruise (internal)<br>捻挫 【ネンザ】 sprain<br>頓挫 【トンザ】 setback, at a standstill or impasse","挫く 【くじく】 to sprain, to twist, to dampen (enthusiasm), to discourage, to dishearten, to dispirit, to depress, to unnerve, to crush<br>挫ける 【くじける】 to be disheartened, to lose heart, to be dispirited, to be crushed (emotionally), to be sprained, to be snapped, to be broken"],
卒:["亠: roof; hat (RTK)　从: two people; assembly line (RTK)　十: ten; cross; needle (RTK)","graduate","GRADUATE, come to an end　PRIVATE, soldier","Ph.D graduation for assembly line of doctors(<em>needles</em>) with the cap and tassel(<em>top hat</em>). It took them <em>10 years</em> (Bachelor's, Masters, PhD) to get there.... :-p.","When you<strong> graduate</strong>, you wear a hat and<strong> graduate</strong> in an assembly line while your parents sit on pins and needles because it will take ten years to pay off those loans.","ソツ、 シュツ","そっ.する、 お.える、 お.わる、 ついに、 にわか","卒 【ソツ】 low-ranking soldier, graduation, outgrowing, moving on (from), low-ranking samurai (1870-1872), death (of a noble, etc.)<br>卒業 【ソツギョウ】 graduation, completion (e.g. of a course), outgrowing something, moving on<br>軽率 【ケイソツ】 rash, thoughtless, careless, hasty, imprudent<br>何卒 【ナニトゾ】 please, kindly, I beg of you, if it pleases you, by all means, without fail","卒する 【そっする】 to die, to pass away<br>終える 【おえる】 to finish, to graduate<br>終わる 【おわる】 to finish, to end, to close"],
傘:["人: human (亻); umbrella (𠆢) (RTK)　从: two people; assembly line (RTK)　从: two people; assembly line (RTK)　十: ten; cross; needle (RTK)","umbrella","UMBRELLA","There are two <em>assembly lines</em> at the<strong> umbrella</strong> factory. One is responsible for making the top of the<strong> umbrella</strong>, and the other for making the handle. The two lines <em>cross</em> at the end, where one man tries frantically to jam the sets of parts together.","FOUR PERSONS can fit under this<strong> UMBRELLA</strong> if they are thin as a NEEDLE.","サン","かさ","傘下 【サンカ】 affiliated with, under jurisdiction of, under the umbrella<br>傘形器官 【サンケイキカン】 bot umbraculum<br>落下傘 【ラッカサン】 parachute<br>開傘 【カイサン】 opening of a parachute","傘 【かさ】 umbrella, parasol<br>傘形碍子 【かさがたがいし】 umbrella insulator<br>核の傘 【かくのかさ】 nuclear umbrella<br>唐傘 【からかさ】 paper umbrella"],
