第:["竹: bamboo (⺮)　弔: condolences　丿: katakana no","No.","ORDINAL NUMBER PREFIX; order","The<strong> No.</strong> 1 currency in the world is the <em>dollar</em>. But, the Asian nations are fast catching up and may in reality have already surpassed it. So, let the <em>bamboo</em> represent the<strong> No.</strong> 2 currencies (the yen, etc.). The reverse order (<em>bamboo</em> on top and the <em>dollar</em> on the bottom) is really a look at the future.","The<strong> No.</strong>1 currency may at one time have been the dollar, but since the economic slowdown the <em>weak dollar</em> has been overtaken by currencies from <em>bamboo</em> growing countries. (Thanks to Johnnyltn for the idea.) Using the alternate writing of the dollar primitive as weak dollar.","ダイ、 テイ","","第 【ダイ】 ordinal<br>第一 【ダイイチ】 first, foremost, number one<br>次第 【シダイ】 dependent upon, as soon as, immediately (upon), circumstances, order, precedence, program, programme, agenda<br>落第 【ラクダイ】 failure, dropping out of a class<br>邸宅 【テイタク】 mansion, residence",""],
弟:["丷: animal horns (RTK)　弔: condolences　丿: katakana no","younger brother","YOUNGER BROTHER","<strong>Younger brothers</strong> are always more prone to mischief. Mine, you can almost see the little <em>horns</em> on him and the <em>dollar signs</em> on his eyes when he comes up with a money-making scheme.","The<strong> younger brother</strong> was a <em>horny</em> <em>dollar</em> -chasing bastard.","テイ、 ダイ、 デ","おとうと","弟 【オトウト】 younger brother, pupil, apprentice<br>弟子 【デシ】 pupil, disciple, adherent, follower, apprentice, young person, teacher's student-helper<br>兄弟 【キョウダイ】 siblings, brothers and sisters, brothers, siblings-in-law, brothers-in-law, sisters-in-law, mate, friend<br>従兄弟 【イトコ】 cousin (male)<br>兄弟 【キョウダイ】 siblings, brothers and sisters, brothers, siblings-in-law, brothers-in-law, sisters-in-law, mate, friend<br>ご兄弟 【ゴキョウダイ】 siblings, brothers and sisters<br>弟子 【デシ】 pupil, disciple, adherent, follower, apprentice, young person, teacher's student-helper<br>弟子入り 【デシイリ】 apprenticeship, enrolling","弟 【おとうと】 younger brother, pupil, apprentice<br>弟君 【おとうとぎみ】 younger brother"],
巧:["工: craft; construction　丂: snare, slingshot (RTK)","adroit","SKILLFUL, ingenious","<strong>Adroit</strong>: dextrous, deft, skillful. Snare is a little generic so I'll use BEAR TRAP, with huge teeth cartoon style that snares you around the ankle. In the <em>crafting</em> of a <em>bear trap</em>, one must be particularly<strong> adroit</strong>. Otherwise they will become the victim of their down device.","To be <em>adroit</em> one must have mastered the <strong>crafting</strong> of <strong>snares</strong>.","コウ","たく.み、 たく.む、 うま.い","巧妙 【コウミョウ】 ingenious, skillful, clever, deft<br>好走 【コウソウ】 good running<br>利口 【リコウ】 clever, intelligent, wise, bright, sharp, sensible, smart, shrewd, well-behaved (of kids, animals, etc), obedient, good, good (with words)<br>精巧 【セイコウ】 elaborate, delicate, exquisite","巧み 【たくみ】 skill, cleverness<br>巧みな手段 【たくみなしゅだん】 clever trick<br>巧む 【たくむ】 to devise, to plot, to plan<br>旨い 【うまい】 skillful, clever, expert, wise, successful, delicious, appetizing, appetising, fortunate, splendid, promising<br>巧い絵 【うまいえ】 excellent picture (painting)"],
