追:["𠂤: maestro (RTK)　辶: walk; road; way (RTK)","chase","CHASE, follow　","<em>Maestro</em>, coattails flapping wildly, is being <strong>chase</strong>d down the <em>road</em> by his fans.","<em>Maestro</em> primative = <em>James Bond</em>. Here he gives<strong> chase</strong> down the <em>road</em> to the bad guys. I'm thinking of the car<strong> chase</strong> in 'The Man with the Golden Gun' - NOT <a href=\"/study/kanji/%E9%80%90\">逐</a> (<span class=\"frnr\">#539</span>). I think about 'Race N<strong> Chase</strong>' (a scalextric type toy)...there were no pigs in 'Race N<strong> Chase</strong>', only cars.","ツイ","お.う","追加 【ツイカ】 addition, supplement, append (e.g. to a file), appendix<br>追跡 【ツイセキ】 chase, pursuit, tracking, stalking, following up, tracing<br>訴追 【ソツイ】 legal action<br>猛追 【モウツイ】 hot chase (pursuit), hectic chase","追う 【おう】 to chase, to run after, to pursue, to follow (i.e. a set order, a trend), to drive out, to oust, to expel, to drive (i.e. a herd), (in passive voice) to be pressed (for time, etc.)"],
阜:["𠂤: maestro (RTK)　十: ten; cross; needle (RTK)","large hill","MOUND","The <em>maestro</em> lives on top of a<strong> large hill</strong> so that he can play music at over <em>ten</em> decibels without anyone giving a damn.","<strong>Note to those who have not got this far in the book:</strong> This is the full kanji for the <em>Pinnacle</em> primitive (i.e. only the left-hand version of the primitive). The full kanji for the <em>City Walls</em> primitive is <a href=\"/study/kanji/%E9%82%91\">邑</a> (<span class=\"frnr\">#2296</span>). <em>Beyonce</em> went for an invigorating walk up a<strong> large hill</strong> on a summer's afternoon. Since the grass was so lush and cool, she took off her sandals and immediately stepped on a used hypodermic <em>needle</em>. 岐<strong>阜</strong>県　ぎ<strong>ふ</strong>けん Gi<strong>fu</strong> Prefecture.","フ、 フウ","","埠頭 【フトウ】 pier, wharf, quay, dock<br>岐阜 【ギフ】 Gifu (city)<br>陰阜 【インフ】 mons veneris, mons pubis",""],
