髄:["骨: bone; skeleton (RTK)　有: possess　辶: walk; road; way (RTK)","marrow","MARROW","A <em>skeleton</em> is shuffling along the shoulder of the road, so you pull up next to him and ask where he is going. He says he's going to donate his<strong> marrow</strong> to the hospital because he got into some financial trouble and lost everything; his<strong> marrow</strong> is the only thing he still <em>possesses</em>.","Did you know there are road ways in skeleton? Yeah, they are cool, they possess<strong> marrow</strong>.","ズイ","","髄 【ズイ】 medulla, marrow, pith<br>髄膜炎 【ズイマクエン】 meningitis<br>神髄 【シンズイ】 essence, quintessence, spirit, soul, heart, pith, pith and marrow<br>精髄 【セイズイ】 essence, kernel, spirit, pith",""],
禍:["示: altar; show (礻)　咼: evil; jawbone (RTK)","calamity","CALAMITY","Continued from <a href=\"/study/kanji/%E7%A5%A5\">祥</a> (<span class=\"frnr\">#1088</span>). Once a year, the people pray for a sign from the gods. But if the gods are feeling particularly mischievous, they'll send down a <em>jawbone</em> to the <em>altar</em>. The people see this as a sign of<strong> calamity</strong> to come. The gods think of it as an amusing prank.","Truely a<strong> calamity</strong> for an undead wedding, just as he may kiss the bride at the <em>altar</em>, he loses his <em>jawbone</em>.","カ","わざわい","禍福 【カフク】 fortune and misfortune, prosperity and adversity, good and evil, weal and woe<br>禍根 【カコン】 root of evil, source of evil<br>戦禍 【センカ】 war damages, ravages of war<br>惨禍 【サンカ】 calamity","災い 【わざわい】 calamity, catastrophe, misfortune<br>災い転じて福となす 【わざわいてんじてふくとなす】 to turn misfortune into fortune (esp. through one's own efforts), to turn the potential disaster to one's advantage"],
