阪:["阜: hill; pinnacle (RTK) (阝)　反: anti-","Heights","ŌSAKA　SLOPE","If you're scared of <strong>Heights</strong>, you don't want to stay at <em>The Pinnacle</em>; you are <em>anti-</em> <em>The Pinnacle</em>. Primitive: <em>The Pinnacle</em> is a dream-like gated community at the top of a mount. This allows for innumerable stories for all the kanji with this primitive since you have a whole city to work with. Also prevents confusion with \"mountain\".","People are being displaced in 大阪 to make room for a new development, Osaka<strong> Heights</strong>, the <em>pinnacle</em> of modern Japanese housing. An angry mob of protestors are outside with <em>Anti-</em>Osaka<strong> Heights</strong> signs.","ハン","さか","阪神 【ハンシン】 Osaka-Kobe, Hanshin (company name: railway, dept. store, baseball team, etc.)<br>阪神大震災 【ハンシンダイシンサイ】 Great Hanshin Earthquake (Jan 1995)<br>京阪 【ケイハン】 Kyoto-Osaka<br>在阪 【ザイハン】 being in Osaka","坂 【さか】 slope, hill<br>大阪 【おおさか】 Osaka, large hill"],
