踊:["足: leg; wooden leg (⻊) (RTK)　甬: road with walls on both sides","jump","DANCE","The winner of the long<strong> jump</strong> competition was disqualified when they found he used a <em>pogo stick</em> tied to his <em>leg</em> to<strong> jump</strong> further.","The high <strong>jump</strong>er has his <em>wooden leg</em> fitted with a <em>pogo stick</em>, and can now<strong> jump</strong> even higher. (See my note at <a href=\"/study/kanji/%E9%80%9A\">通</a> (<span class=\"frnr\">#1408</span>) for <em>pogo stick</em>). EDIT (2 years later): Keyword \"jump\" leads to confusion later on (see cjon256's post), <strong>\"Dancing\"</strong> would be better (but be sure to keep it distinct from <a href=\"/study/kanji/%E8%88%9E\">舞</a> (<span class=\"frnr\">#1774</span>)). New Story: I was no good at <strong>dancing</strong> due to my <em>wooden leg</em>... until I had it fitted with a <em>pogo stick</em>!","ヨウ","おど.る","踊躍 【ヨウヤク】 leaping with joy, jumping about<br>舞踊 【ブヨウ】 dancing, dance<br>現代舞踊 【ゲンダイブヨウ】 contemporary dance, modern dance","踊る 【おどる】 to dance (orig. a hopping dance)<br>踊る阿呆に見る阿呆 【おどるあほうにみるあほう】 dancing fool, watching fool, you're a fool if you dance, and a fool if you just look on, all fools, so let's all dance"],
疑:["匕: spoon　矢: arrow; dart (RTK)　マ: ma; chop-seal (RTK)　疋: cloth; zoo; mending (RTK)","doubt","DOUBT, distrust","(Katsuo) You come at the zoo entrance. 'Here sir, a spoon to feed the animals.' cool 'and a dart(gun) in case stuff go wrong' ....' please chop-seal (sign) here for in case of accidents the zoo is not responsible.' 'lion feeding time is. bla bla' You are having serious<strong> doubt</strong>s about if you still want to go into this zoo.","A very<strong> doubt</strong>ful story: At the entrance to my local zoo they issue you with a special <em>spoon</em> (to feed the animals) and a <em>dart</em> gun (to defend yourself in case of animal attack). You must then <em>hanko</em> (<em>seal</em>) a document to say you’ve received both these items, only after which will they let you enter the <em>zoo</em>. (Oh, and if you forget your hanko, I<strong> doubt</strong> they’ll let you in).","ギ","うたが.う","疑 【ギ】 doubt, distrust, suspicion (of)<br>疑問 【ギモン】 question, problem, doubt, guess<br>容疑 【ヨウギ】 suspicion, charge<br>嫌疑 【ケンギ】 suspicion","疑う 【うたがう】 to doubt, to distrust, to be suspicious of, to suspect"],
