酎:["酉: alcohol　寸: measurement; glue (RTK)","hooch","SHOCHU (Japanese distilled liquor)","While the keyword is \"hooch\", this usually means 焼酎. It has similar effect as whiskey and sniffing glue has: you get intoxicated.","Tastes like whiskey, smells like glue? Then it must be しょうちゅうの「ちゅう」 (<strong> hooch</strong> ). - There you go, reading meaning and a catchy ad jingle, all in one. Possibly the best story I've written. ^^.","チュウ、 チュ","かも.す","酎 【チュウ】 shochu<br>酎ハイ 【チュウハイ】 shochu highball, cocktail of shochu with tonic water<br>焼酎 【ショウチュウ】 shochu, Japanese spirit distilled from sweet potatoes, rice, etc.<br>麦焼酎 【ムギショウチュウ】 shochu distilled from barley<br>酎 【チュウ】 shochu<br>酎ハイ 【チュウハイ】 shochu highball, cocktail of shochu with tonic water",""],
酵:["酉: alcohol　孝: filial piety","fermentation","FERMENT","The secrets of<strong> fermentation</strong> are passed to the son who displays the most filial piety.","Since <em>filial piety</em> is all about respecting ones elders, and the older a <em>whiskey bottle</em> is (i.e. the time it have spent undergoing<strong> fermentation</strong>) the more respect you should give it, the meaning of this kanji becomes clear. If it doesn't, sink back some whiskey and it will.","コウ","","酵素 【コウソ】 enzyme<br>酵母 【コウボ】 yeast, leaven<br>発酵 【ハッコウ】 fermentation, zymosis<br>アルコール発酵 【アルコールハッコウ】 alcohol fermentation",""],
