碑:["石: stone; rock (RTK)　卑: lowly","tombstone","MONUMENT","There is a grave of a <em>lowly</em> man with a<strong> tombstone</strong> made of a simple, small <em>stone</em>. If you bow really low you can read the very small inscription engraved on the <em>stone</em>, it says - “Now that you bowed so low to read this, you are as <em>lowly</em> as I once was”.","A STONE makes a LOWLY<strong> TOMBSTONE</strong>.","ヒ","いしぶみ","碑文 【ヒブン】 inscription, epitaph, epigraph<br>碑石 【ヒセキ】 stone monument<br>記念碑 【キネンヒ】 commemorative plaque (usu. on a stone), stone monument (bearing an inscription)<br>墓碑 【ボヒ】 gravestone, tombstone","碑 【いしぶみ】 stone monument bearing an inscription (esp. memorial for future generations), stele, stela"],
陸:["阜: hill; pinnacle (RTK) (阝)　圥: mushroom; rice seedlings (RTK)　土: ground; land; soil","land","LAND","My rice-seedlings have become sentient and will go on a mission. I can only apologise for the next 6 frames. In the distance, there is a <em>pinnacle</em>, which the newly-awakened <em>rice-seedlings</em> who are still stuck in the <em>ground</em> can see. Could it be the Promised<strong> Land</strong>?","(圥 is the rare kanji for a mushroom. Sticking out of the <em>ground</em> like little knubby <em>legs</em>, it's pretty easy to remember.) Story ~ The<strong> land</strong> around <em>The Pinnacle</em> has <em>mushrooms</em> covering the <em>ground</em>.","リク、 ロク","おか","陸 【リク】 land, shore<br>陸軍 【リクグン】 army<br>大陸 【タイリク】 continent, continental Asia (esp. mainland China), continental Europe<br>着陸 【チャクリク】 landing, alighting, touch down<br>六 【ロク】 six<br>陸 【ロク】 six (used in legal documents)<br>碌碌 【ロクロク】 hardly, barely, inadequately (with negative grammatical constructions)<br>双六 【スゴロク】 sugoroku, traditional Japanese board game played with dice","陸 【りく】 land, shore<br>丘 【おか】 hill, height, knoll, rising ground, bonus points awarded to the winner at the end of a game"],
