熱:["圥: mushroom; rice seedlings (RTK)　土: ground; land; soil　丸: round; fatman (RTK)　火: fire (灬)","heat","HEAT, hot","<a href=\"/study/kanji/%E9%99%B8\">陸</a> (<span class=\"frnr\">#1513</span>) The <em>rice-seedlings</em> (newly freed from the ground but with <em>soil</em> still clinging to their roots) gather in a circle <em>around</em> an <em>oven fire</em>. They need to<strong> heat</strong> up prior to their journey (presumably plants can't walk if they're too cold?)","<strong>Heat</strong> up those RICE SEEDLINGS you pulled from the SOIL in a ROUND pan over a low FLAME. (Note: the hot pan image helps reinforce the idea that this kanji for \"atsui\" refers to something hot to the touch, as opposed to hot weather).","ネツ","あつ.い","熱 【ネツ】 heat, fever, temperature, zeal, passion, enthusiasm, mania, craze, rage<br>熱意 【ネツイ】 zeal, enthusiasm<br>加熱 【カネツ】 heating, application of heat<br>情熱 【ジョウネツ】 passion, enthusiasm, zeal","熱い 【あつい】 hot (thing), passionate (feelings, etc.), ardent, hot (e.g. gaze), hot (e.g. temper), zealous, enthusiastic, fired up, intense, severe, extreme, hot (topic), of interest<br>熱い暗黒物質 【あついあんこくぶっしつ】 hot dark matter"],
菱:["艸: grass; plants; flowers (艹, 龷)　圥: mushroom; rice seedlings (RTK)　夂: winter; walking legs (RTK)","diamond","RHOMBUS","Some girls want<strong> diamond</strong>s, but others will be satisfied with just <em>flowers</em>. However if you think you can win her over with <em>rice seedlings</em>, expect her to get up on her <em>walking legs</em> and walk on out!","<a href=\"/study/kanji/%E9%99%B8\">陸</a> (<span class=\"frnr\">#1513</span>) Deciding to use the<strong> diamond</strong>-shaped water caltrop <em>flower</em> as cover/protection, the <em>rice-seedlings</em> with their <em>walking legs</em> (now free from soil), can start their journey.","リョウ","ひし","菱亜鉛鉱 【リョウアエンコウ】 smithsonite, zinc spar, szaskaite, calamine, dry-bone ore<br>菱苦土鉱 【リョウクドコウ】 magnesite","菱 【ひし】 Trapa japonica (species of plant closely related to water chestnut or water caltrop), caltrop (weapon), caltrap<br>菱垣廻船 【ひがきかいせん】 large Japanese junk"],
陵:["阜: hill; pinnacle (RTK) (阝)　圥: mushroom; rice seedlings (RTK)　夂: winter; walking legs (RTK)","mausoleum","IMPERIAL MAUSOLEUM, hill","<a href=\"/study/kanji/%E9%99%B8\">陸</a> (<span class=\"frnr\">#1513</span>) However, the <em>pinnacle</em> that the <em>rice-seedlings</em> finally reach with the use of their <em>walking legs</em> turns out not to be the Promised Land after all, but simply a<strong> mausoleum</strong> (containing many dead rice-seedlings exhausted from previous quests?). Oh no!","On top of <em>The Pinnacle</em> is a <strong>masoleum</strong> for rice seedling farmers. They make an annual <em>walking</em> pilgrimage there.","リョウ","みささぎ","陵 【ミササギ】 imperial mausoleum, Emperor's tomb, big hill<br>陵墓 【リョウボ】 imperial tomb or mausoleum<br>丘陵 【キュウリョウ】 hill<br>帝陵 【テイリョウ】 imperial mausoleum","陵 【みささぎ】 imperial mausoleum, Emperor's tomb, big hill"],
亥:["亥: boar; acorn (RTK)","sign of the hog","(sign of) THE BOAR","A greedy hog in a top hat who has eaten all of the acorns. He even elbows people out of the way to get them.","Top Hat + Elbow + Person: The<strong> sign of the hog</strong> was a very recognizable tattoo - a hog with a big grin in a <em>top hat</em>, sticking his <em>elbow</em> into the <em>person</em> next to him.","ガイ、 カイ","い","亥月 【ガイゲツ】 tenth month of the lunar calendar<br>丁亥 【テイガイ】 24th of the sexagenary cycle<br>己亥 【ツチノトイ】 thirty-sixth of the sexagenary cycle","亥 【い】 twelfth sign of the Chinese zodiac (The Boar, 9pm-11pm, north-northwest, October)<br>亥年 【いどし】 year of the boar<br>丁亥 【ていがい】 24th of the sexagenary cycle<br>己亥 【つちのとい】 thirty-sixth of the sexagenary cycle"],
核:["木: tree; wood　亥: boar; acorn (RTK)","nucleus","NUCLEUS, core","The<strong> nucleus</strong> of an oak TREE is an ACORN.","In the<strong> nucleus</strong> of the acorn, all the DNA is stored -- the building blocks for a new tree.","カク","","核 【カク】 pit (of a fruit), stone, core, nucleus, nuclear, nuclear weaponry<br>核シェルター 【カクシェルター】 nuclear bomb shelter<br>中心核 【チュウシンカク】 core (of planets, stars, galaxies, etc.), nucleus (of comets, galaxies, etc.)<br>原子核 【ゲンシカク】 nucleus (atomic)",""],
刻:["亥: boar; acorn (RTK)　刀: sword; dagger, saber (RTK) (刂)","engrave","ENGRAVE, carve　POINT IN TIME","This famous ninja (I always use ninjas with <em>sabres</em>, distinct from samurai) used to<strong> engrave</strong> the kanji for his name onto <em>acorns</em>, and throw the <em>acorns</em> to distract his enemies. The legend goes that by the time his victims would pick up the <em>acorn</em> and read the<strong> engrave</strong>d kanji, they were already dead.","While it's traditional for lovers to<strong> engrave</strong> their names on a tree in many countries, in Japan, however, it was traditional for a samurai to signify his undying love for a woman by engraving the kanji of her name on an <em>acorn</em> with his <em>sabre</em>.","コク","きざ.む、 きざ.み","刻 【コク】 archaic period of time (usu. a period of approx. two hours corresponding to one of the signs of the Chinese zodiac), carving, engraving, cutting, mincing, victory, strictness, cruelty<br>刻々 【コッコク】 moment by moment, hour by hour<br>深刻 【シンコク】 serious, severe, grave, acute<br>時刻 【ジコク】 instant, time, moment","刻む 【きざむ】 to mince, to cut fine, to chop up, to hash, to shred, to carve, to engrave, to chisel, to notch, to tick away (time), to record the passing moments, to etch (into one's mind), to remember distinctly, to have tattooed, to torment<br>刻み 【きざみ】 shredded tobacco, notch, nick<br>刻み付ける 【きざみつける】 to engrave, to carve out"],
