序:["广: cave (RTK)　予: beforehand","preface","INTRODUCTORY PART, beginning　ORDER, sequence","The<strong> preface</strong> to all human history was written <em>beforehand</em> in <em>caves</em>.","Rename the \"beforehand\" part to be <em>glove</em> (because you have to wear <em>gloves</em> beforehand if you want to wield the halberd, which is why this primitive is an incomplete halberd). The story: a winter morning. A textbook author is holed up in his tiny office, a veritable <em>cave</em>. He wants to start his masterpiece textbook by first writing the<strong> preface</strong>. But he can't get started. He sits and stares at empty paper until evening. It gets cold and he puts on <em>glove</em>s, shivering, but still unable to start his<strong> preface</strong>.","ジョ","つい.で、 ついで","序 【ジョ】 order, ordering, beginning, start, foreword, preface, introduction, (in gagaku or noh) opening of a song<br>序文 【ジョブン】 preface, foreword, introduction<br>順序 【ジュンジョ】 order, sequence, procedure<br>秩序 【チツジョ】 order, regularity, system, method","序 【ついで】 opportunity, occasion<br>序でに 【ついでに】 incidentally, taking the opportunity, while (you) are at it, on the occasion<br>序 【ついで】 opportunity, occasion<br>序でに 【ついでに】 incidentally, taking the opportunity, while (you) are at it, on the occasion"],
