閣:["門: gate　各: each; every","tower","STATELY BUILDING　CABINET (of a government)","To keep this distinct from other kanji such as \"watchtower\" and \"pagoda\", I use the mnemonic \"<em>towering<strong> tower</strong></em>\". -- In some old 8-bit kung-fu videogame, with a plot similar as Bruce Lee's last, unfinished movie, the hero must break through a <em>gate</em> at <em>each</em> level of the<strong> tower</strong>ing<strong> tower</strong>, fighting with opponents using various styles of kung-fu until he meets the finale at the topmost level of the \"towering<strong> tower</strong>\".","Remember the two<strong> tower</strong>s from lord of the rings... <em>each</em> has it's own - very difficult to master - entrance <em>gate</em>.","カク","","閣僚 【カクリョウ】 cabinet ministers<br>閣議 【カクギ】 cabinet meeting<br>内閣 【ナイカク】 cabinet, (government) ministry<br>楼閣 【ロウカク】 multistoried building",""],
