幹:["𠦝: mist (RTK)　人: human (亻); umbrella (𠆢) (RTK)　干: dry","tree trunk","TRUNK","A fine <em>mist</em> is falling, and so everyone gathers around near the tree-trunk, effectively using the rest of the tree as an <em>umbrella</em> in order to keep <em>dry</em>.","By astridtops - In the rainy <em>mist</em>, Totoro is standing in front of a tree-trunk at the bus stop, under the <em>umbrella</em> he just received. Look at him smiling: even when the big drops fall, he remains <em>dry</em>! Great story...which I get to by thinking: tree-trunk-&gt;<strong>TT</strong> -&gt;<strong>T</strong>onari no <strong>T</strong>otoro. I also imagine Mickey Mouse is there too as the KUNyomi for this kanji is みき.","カン","みき","幹 【ミキ】 (tree) trunk, (arrow) shaft, (tool) handle, backbone, base<br>幹部 【カンブ】 management, (executive) staff, leaders, leadership, top brass, upper echelons<br>主幹 【シュカン】 chief editor, managing editor, manager, person in charge<br>基幹 【キカン】 mainstay, nucleus, key","幹 【みき】 (tree) trunk, (arrow) shaft, (tool) handle, backbone, base"],
