繭:["艸: grass; plants; flowers (艹, 龷)　冂: hood; belt (RTK)　糸: thread; Spider-Man (RTK)　虫: insect","cocoon","COCOON","This is a simple two-column manga showing the metamorphosis of a caterpillar into a<strong> cocoon</strong>. First, the caterpillar gets under a large flower (bees tend to hang around flowers, which scare away other predators). Then, in the first frame, we see the caterpillar (<em>insect</em>). Then, a bar separating this frame from the next frame (remember that Japanese manga run the other way!), in which we see the <em>insect</em> covered with <em>thread</em>, making a beautiful<strong> cocoon</strong>.","I dont like lesson 51 so far.","ケン","まゆ、 きぬ","絹糸 【ケンシ】 silk thread<br>繭価 【マユカ】 price of a cocoon<br>黄繭 【コウケン】 yellow cocoon<br>収繭 【シュウケン】 cocoon crop","繭 【まゆ】 cocoon<br>繭価 【まゆか】 price of a cocoon<br>黄繭 【こうけん】 yellow cocoon<br>屑繭 【くずまゆ】 waste cocoon (silk), bad cocoon, damaged cocoon<br>絹糸 【けんし】 silk thread"],
益:["䒑: weeds　ハ: animal legs (RTK)　皿: dish","benefit","BENEFIT, profit","The<strong> benefit</strong> of having sharp <em>horns</em> and fast <em>legs</em> is that an animal can get to the food <em>dish</em> first.","The<strong> benefit</strong> of being an animal with <em>horns</em> and fast <em>legs</em> is in keeping it from becoming a <em>dish</em> for the other animals! (shaydwyrm).","エキ、 ヤク","ま.す","益 【エキ】 benefit, use, good, advantage, gain, profit, gains<br>益する 【エキスル】 to benefit (someone), to be useful<br>利益 【リエキ】 profit, gains, benefit, advantage, interest (of the public, etc.), grace (of God, Buddha, etc.) (esp. as attained through rightful actions, prayer, adherence to one's faith, etc.), blessing, miracle<br>有益 【ユウエキ】 beneficial, profitable<br>益 【エキ】 benefit, use, good, advantage, gain, profit, gains<br>益体もない 【ヤクタイモナイ】 useless, worthless, absurd, baloney<br>利益 【リエキ】 profit, gains, benefit, advantage, interest (of the public, etc.), grace (of God, Buddha, etc.) (esp. as attained through rightful actions, prayer, adherence to one's faith, etc.), blessing, miracle<br>御利益 【ゴリヤク】 grace (of God), divine favour, blessing, miracle, answer to a prayer, benefit, efficacy","益々 【ますます】 increasingly, more and more, decreasingly (when declining), less and less<br>丈夫 【じょうふ】 hero, manly person, warrior<br>益々 【ますます】 increasingly, more and more, decreasingly (when declining), less and less"],
暇:["日: day; sun　叚: False","spare time","FREE TIME","Some jackass-like people have way too much<strong> spare time</strong>. You can find video's of them all over the internet, if you like such things, you can watch it all <em>day</em>. You see them <em>stapling</em> their <em>mouths</em> shut, or throwing eachother <em>upside down in boxes</em> or kicking each other in the <em>crotch</em>.","Tip: The complex right side of this kanji appears twice more in Heisig. He later names it \"hobby\". REF: <a href=\"/study/kanji/%E8%9D%A6\">蝦</a> (<span class=\"frnr\">#2689</span>), <a href=\"/study/kanji/%E9%9C%9E\">霞</a> (<span class=\"frnr\">#2779</span>).","カ","ひま、 いとま","暇人 【ヒマジン】 person with a lot of free time on their hands, person of leisure, idler<br>休暇 【キュウカ】 holiday, day off, furlough, absence (from work)<br>余暇 【ヨカ】 leisure, leisure time, spare time","暇 【ひま】 spare time, free time, leisure, time (e.g. time it takes to do something), time off, day off, vacation, holiday, leave, quitting (one's job), firing someone, divorcing (one's spouse), (of one's time) free, (of one's business) slow, leaving, departing<br>暇つぶし 【ひまつぶし】 waste of time, killing time<br>手間暇 【てまひま】 time and effort, trouble<br>暇暇 【ひまひま】 one's leisure hours<br>暇 【ひま】 spare time, free time, leisure, time (e.g. time it takes to do something), time off, day off, vacation, holiday, leave, quitting (one's job), firing someone, divorcing (one's spouse), (of one's time) free, (of one's business) slow, leaving, departing<br>暇乞い 【いとまごい】 leave-taking, offering one's resignation, farewell visit<br>お暇 【おいとま】 leaving, going home, quitting one's job, free time, leisure, spare time"],
