禅:["示: altar; show (礻)　単: simple","Zen","ZEN","Knowing<strong> ZEN</strong>’s emphasis on “nothingness,” it’s not hard to envision a<strong> ZEN</strong> ALTAR being quite clean and SIMPLE.","<em>Simple-minded blond girl</em> (see frame 1928) is very good at<strong> Zen</strong>, which isn't surprising since she doesn't think much. She has this bad habit of meditating perched on the main temple <em>altar</em>, which infuriates the<strong> Zen</strong> buddhists. When they get up to her and tell her rudely to step down the <em>altar</em>, she just smiles and teases them : \"Not very<strong> zen</strong> are you ?\". Who would have thought <em>simple-minded blond girl</em> would teach the<strong> Zen</strong> buddhists a lesson !","ゼン、 セン","しずか、 ゆず.る","禅 【ゼン】 dhyana (profound meditation), Zen (Buddhism)<br>禅坊主 【ゼンボウズ】 Zen monk<br>座禅 【ザゼン】 zazen (seated Zen meditation, usu. in a cross-legged position)<br>吹禅 【スイゼン】 Zen blowing meditation (performed with shakuhachi)",""],
