剛:["岡: mount　刀: sword; dagger, saber (RTK) (刂)","sturdy","TOUGH, strong","Mount everest is very<strong> sturdy</strong>, you can hit it all day with a saber and it wont even wobble.","Anything<strong> sturdy</strong> in Japan is associated with <em>Mount</em> Fuji. Perhaps this is because it's symmetry is believed to make it rather<strong> sturdy</strong> itself, unlike all those crooked mountains that are around and tend to fall apart (think rock slides, avalanches, etc.). Here we see<strong> Sturdy</strong>-brand <em>sabers</em> with <em>Mount</em> Fuji engraved on the blade.","ゴウ","","剛 【ゴウ】 strong, hard, manly<br>強情 【ゴウジョウ】 obstinacy, stubbornness<br>外柔内剛 【ガイジュウナイゴウ】 gentle but firm<br>強豪 【キョウゴウ】 veteran, champion",""],
