喧:["口: mouth　宣: proclaim; say; announce","clamor","CLAMOROUS","To<strong> clamor</strong> means to open your <em>mouth</em> and <em>proclaim</em> loudly your opinions.","I picture those guys on the street in Japan with a megaphone next to their mouth proclaiming something very loudly and creating a<strong> clamor</strong> being totally annoying.","ケン","やかま.しい、 かまびす.しい","喧嘩 【ケンカ】 quarrel, brawl, fight, squabble, scuffle, argument<br>喧騒 【ケンソウ】 tumult, great noise, clatter, hustle and bustle","喧しい 【やかましい】 noisy, boisterous, strict, faultfinding, carping, fussy<br>喧しい 【やかましい】 noisy, boisterous, strict, faultfinding, carping, fussy"],
叩:["口: mouth　卩: seal; stamp; (㔾) fingerprint (RTK)","bash","STRIKE, slap","These &amp;^% <em>stamps</em> won't stay fixed to the envelop when I lick them with my <em>mouth</em>. No matter how hard I<strong> bash</strong> them, they come loose every time. Aargh!","For me, the kanji looks like a picture of two eyes. Somebody<strong> bash</strong>ed the right one until it burst open. Ugh... Put a stamp on it - I don't want to see it!","コウ","たた.く、 はた.く、 すぎ","叩首 【コウシュ】 kowtow<br>叩頭 【コウトウ】 kowtow (bow made from a kneeling position wherein the forehead touches the ground)","叩く 【たたく】 to strike, to clap, to knock, to dust, to beat, to play drums, to abuse, to flame (e.g. on the Internet), to insult, to use up money, to call, to invoke (e.g. a function)<br>叩く 【たたく】 to strike, to clap, to knock, to dust, to beat, to play drums, to abuse, to flame (e.g. on the Internet), to insult, to use up money, to call, to invoke (e.g. a function)"],
