掴:["手: hand; fingers (扌) (RTK)　国: country","clutch","GRASP, clutch","Reminds me of a Star Wars quote, Leia: \"The more you tighten your grip, Tarkin, the more star systems will slip through your <em>fingers</em>.\" (i.e., the tighter you <strong>clutch</strong>, the more <em>countries</em> you'll lose).","<strong>Clutch</strong> tightly with your <em>fingers</em> your passport so you can get back in the <em>country</em> without any issues.","カク","つか.む、 つか.まえる、 つか.まる","","掴む 【つかむ】 to seize, to catch, to grasp, to grip, to grab, to hold, to catch hold of, to lay one's hands on, to clutch, to understand, to grasp, to comprehend<br>捕まえる 【つかまえる】 to catch, to arrest, to seize<br>捕まる 【つかまる】 to be caught, to be arrested, to hold on to, to grasp, to find (e.g. proof), to get (e.g. a taxi), to be detained by"],
捺:["","impress","","In <em>Nara</em>, they do not accept はんこ, in fact their seals are done by simply <strong>impressing</strong> <em>fingers</em> into hot melting wax (fingerprints are unique!).","In <em>Nara</em>, you<strong> impress</strong> wax seals with just your <em>finger</em>.","ナツ、 ダツ","さ.す、 お.す","捺印 【ナツイン】 affixing a seal<br>押捺 【オウナツ】 sealing (document)<br>指紋押捺 【シモンオウナツ】 fingerprinting","押す 【おす】 to push, to press, to apply pressure from above, to press down, to stamp (i.e. a passport), to apply a seal, to affix (e.g. gold leaf), to press (someone for something), to urge, to compel, to influence, to overwhelm, to overpower, to repress, to push (events along), to advance (a plan), to do in spite of ..., to do even though ..., to force, to make sure, to be pressed for time, to advance troops, to attack, (of light) to be diffused across an entire surface"],
