渾:["","gushing","","As the Pharaoh's <em>chariots</em> tried to cross the Red Sea,<strong> gushing</strong> <em>waters</em> came and crushed them.","Picture yourself driving a <em>chariot</em> wildly down the street and knocking over all the fire hydrants. <em>Water</em> is<strong> gushing</strong> everywhere.","コン","すべ.て、 にご.る","渾名 【アダナ】 nickname<br>渾身 【コンシン】 with all one's might, with one's whole body<br>雄渾 【ユウコン】 magnificent, sublime, vigorous, bold<br>滾々 【コンコン】 copious (flowing)",""],
涜:["","blaspheme","","The church is <em>selling</em> holy <em>water</em> for the faithful, but if you dare to say its tap water, they'd tell you you were <strong>blaspheming</strong>.","During the Wedding at Cana, the Son of God had some people come up to complain after he performed his miracle. \"This wine is terrible! Are you trying to <em>sell</em> me <em>watered</em>-down wine?\" He replied, \"It's a wedding, for God's sake, the wine is free, so stop complaining.\" The dissatisfied guest retorted, \"Hey, don't<strong> blaspheme</strong>!\" Jesus Christ just rolled his eyes and, under his breath, uttered his own name in vain.","トク、 トウ","けが.す、 けが.れ、 みぞ","涜職 【トクショク】 corruption, bribery<br>涜神 【トクシン】 blasphemy<br>冒涜 【ボウトク】 blasphemy, curse, profanity, sacrilege, desecration<br>汚涜 【オトク】 blasphemy, desecration",""],
梁:["","roofbeam","","What seemed to be <em>water</em> dripping from the <em>wooden</em><strong> roofbeam</strong> was actually <em>drops</em> of blood dripping from a <em>sword</em> lodged in it.","A while back, I was goofing around with my <em>sword</em> when I accidentally lodged it in the<strong> roofbeam</strong>. Apparently, I also poked a couple of holes in the roof because whenever it rains, some <em>water</em> drips onto the floor - <em>one drop from each side of the sword</em>. So that's why there is a <em>tree</em> growing on the floor now. :/.","リョウ","はり、 うつばり、 うちばり、 やな、 はし","梁 【リョウ】 Liang Dynasty (of China)<br>梁山泊 【リョウザンパク】 place of assemblage for the bold and ambitious<br>棟梁 【トウリョウ】 chief support, pillar (e.g. of nation), leader, boss, master (craftsman), beams and ridge supports of a roof (orig. meaning)<br>橋梁 【キョウリョウ】 bridge","梁 【はり】 beam, joist<br>梁成 【はりせい】 height of a beam, beam as measured from top to bottom"],
澱:["","sediment","","<em>Mr.</em> President is visiting the city of New Orleans, where the<strong> sediment</strong> is being cleared away that got there when the <em>water</em> rushed in during hurricane Katrina.","After Mr. (and Mrs.) Smith blasted everything in sight with a missile launcher (see <a href=\"/study/kanji/%E6%AE%BF\">殿</a> (<span class=\"frnr\">#1945</span>)), turning the whole world into<strong> sediment</strong>, nothing was left to shot at. The only thing left was <em>WATER</em>. So boring...","デン、 テン","おり、 ど.ろ、 よど.み、 よど.む","でん粉 【デンプン】 starch<br>澱粉質 【デンプンシツ】 starchiness, starchy, farinaceous<br>沈澱 【チンデン】 precipitation, deposition, settlement (e.g. of sediment)","澱 【おり】 dregs, lees, grounds, sediment<br>淀み 【よどみ】 stagnation, deposit, sediment, backwater, faltering, hesitation, pause<br>淀み無い 【よどみない】 fluent, smooth, flowing<br>澱む 【よどむ】 to stagnate, to be stagnant, to settle, to deposit, to be sedimented, to be precipitated, to hesitate, to be sluggish, to stammer, to stumble, to falter"],
洛:["","old Kyoto","","<strong>Old Kyoto</strong> was once the capital, but if has <em>fall</em>en from grace and the flowers that used to decorate its houses have all disapeared.","(+nolusu)<strong> Old Kyoto</strong> once had a beautiful sign decorated with <em>flowers</em> saying \"Welcome to Kyoto!\". But over time, the <em>flowers</em> have <em>fallen</em> off. (compare <a href=\"/study/kanji/%E8%90%BD\">落</a> (<span class=\"frnr\">#320</span>)).","ラク","","洛外 【ラクガイ】 outside Kyoto or the capital<br>洛学 【ラクガク】 Luo Xue school (neo-Confucianist school)<br>京洛 【キョウラク】 capital (esp. Kyoto)<br>入洛 【ジュラク】 proceeding to Kyoto, entering Kyoto",""],
汝:["","thou","","One of the modern commandments: \"Thou shalt not imagine wet women, dripping in their bathing suits\".","\"O Romeo, Romeo, wherefore art<strong> thou</strong> Romeo?\" says Juliet, her eyes all watery.","ジョ","なんじ、 なれ、 い、 うぬ、 いまし、 し、 しゃ、 な、 なむち、 まし、 みまし","爾汝 【ジジョ】 you, thou","汝 【なんじ】 thou, you<br>汝自身を知れ 【なんじじしんをしれ】 Know thyself<br>汝 【なむち】 you<br>汝 【い】 you<br>汝 【いまし】 you<br>汝 【うぬ】 blockhead!, you<br>汝等 【うぬら】 ye, you, me, I, us, we<br>汝 【いまし】 you<br>其 【し】 that, you, oneself, themself<br>汝 【い】 you<br>汝 【い】 you<br>己 【な】 I, you<br>汝 【なんじ】 thou, you<br>汝 【なむち】 you<br>汝 【なむち】 you<br>汝 【みまし】 you"],
漉:["","filter","","I<strong> filter</strong> my <em>water</em> using a <em>deer</em>. Sure I'm a naturalist, but you know what? The<strong> filter</strong>ed yellow \"water\" tastes MUCH better!","When you go out into the wilderness, you shouldn't drink fresh <em>water</em> no matter how clean and clear it looks. A <em>deer</em> could have just crapped in it a mile upstream. Lesson: Bring some kind of<strong> filter</strong> to<strong> filter</strong> your drinking <em>water</em>.","ロク","こ.し、 こ.す、 す.く","","漉油 【こしあぶら】 Acanthopanax sciadophylloides (species of flowering plant related to the aralias)<br>漉油の木 【こしあぶらのき】 Acanthopanax sciadophylloides (species of flowering plant related to the aralias)<br>濾す 【こす】 to filter, to strain<br>梳く 【すく】 to comb (out), to card, to untangle (hair)<br>漉く 【すく】 to make something (i.e. paper) from wet, pulpy material by spreading it thin and drying it"],
瀕:["","on the verge of","","<em>Water</em> dripping <em>repeatedly</em> on someone is enough to put them<strong> on the verge of</strong> insanity.","I was<strong> on the verge of</strong> <em>wetting</em> myself when she <em>repeatedly</em> showed me her...","ヒン","ほとり","瀕死 【ヒンシ】 dying, (on the) verge of death<br>瀕する 【ヒンスル】 to be on the verge of, to be about to, to be on the point of",""],
濠:["","moat","","A<strong> moat</strong> is a <em>water</em> structure used against something potentially <em>overpowering</em>.","Australia was designed as a<strong> moat</strong>, surrounded by <em>water</em>, to keep out the <em>overpowering</em> forces of foreign nations.","ゴウ、 コウ","ほり","壕 【ゴウ】 moat, fosse, trench, ditch, underground air-raid shelter, dugout<br>豪 【ゴウ】 Australia<br>環濠 【カンゴウ】 (circular) moat<br>水濠 【スイゴウ】 water jump (on a racetrack, etc.), moat (around a castle, etc.)","堀 【ほり】 moat, fosse, canal, ditch"],
