蓬:["","wormwood","","You bring a<strong> wormwood</strong> <em>flower</em> to a <a href=\"/study/kanji/%E9%80%A2\">逢</a> (<span class=\"frnr\">#2497</span>) for the bitter parting at the end.","<strong>Wormwood</strong> brings very, very vivid and hallucinogenic dreams. You eat some of the intoxicating <em>flowers</em> of the<strong> wormwood</strong> with your girlfriend...and in your high state of mind, decide that it would be a good idea to do it in the bushes on the side of <em>Mario Kart Road</em>. Suddenly, in the middle of it, she starts tripping out, and <em>runs through the bushes</em> into the middle of the track, while they are racing...and is killed. Imagine waking up from that dream...or was it a dream? Sticks for me anyway.","ホウ、 ブ","よもぎ","蓬客 【ホウカク】 wanderer, drifter<br>蓬窓 【ホウソウ】 window with a view of a Japanese mugwort thicket, poor house, humble house, primitive house","蓬 【よもぎ】 Japanese mugwort (Artemisia princeps, Artemisia indica var. maximowiczii), general term for plants in the Artemisia genus, mugwort, sagebrush, wormwood<br>蓬生 【よもぎう】 wasteland, area overgrown with weeds<br>大蓬 【おおよもぎ】 Artemisia montana<br>タカ蓬 【タカよもぎ】 Artemisia selengensis"],
