碇:["","grapnel","","A<strong> grapnel</strong> is a small anchor with several hooks, used for anchoring small boats, or to pull up sunken objects (it looks very much like a grappling hook). The position of <em>stones</em> underwater <em>determines</em> where the<strong> grapnel</strong> will catch.","He was <em>determined</em> to climb this <em>rock</em>, so he used a<strong> grapnel</strong>.","テイ","いかり","停泊 【テイハク】 anchorage, moorings<br>碇置 【テイチ】 anchorage","錨 【いかり】 anchor<br>碇草 【いかりそう】 horny goat weed (Epimedium grandiflorum var. thunbergianum)"],
碧:["","blue-green","","Notes: 珀 (not in Heisig) means \"amber\". Story for both: A bus is stopped at some traffic lights in Japan. Inside, <em>King</em> Henry VIII and Barry <em>White</em> are arguing over whether the lights are yellow or <em>amber</em>. The lights change to \"Go\", and Mick Jagger (<em>stone</em>) then joins a new argument over whether the lights are blue or green. They compromise on<strong> blue-green</strong>.","The rarest form of <em>amber</em> is a<strong> blue-green</strong> <em>stone</em>. (http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Blue_amber).","ヘキ、 ヒャク","","碧雲 【ヘキウン】 bluish cloud, azure sky, blue sky<br>碧眼 【ヘキガン】 blue eyes",""],
硯:["","inkstone","","This is not an ordinary <em>rock</em>, if you look carefully you will <em>see</em> that it is an ancient<strong> inkstone</strong>.","A magical<strong> inkstone</strong> was made in ancient China that was able to mix invisible ink. When the ink dried, the surface it adhered to became invisible. Unfortunately, someone used it once and forgot to wash the <em>stone</em> thoroughly afterwards, and when the ink dried the magical<strong> inkstone</strong> was never <em>seen</em> again.","ケン、 ゲン","すずり","","硯 【すずり】 inkstone<br>硯洗い 【すずりあらい】 event where schoolchildren wash their inkstones, brushes and desks the night before Tanabata to pray for success in their studies"],
砥:["","grindstone","","In Bedrock, people had <em>business cards</em> made of <em>rock</em> and engraved using a<strong> grindstone</strong>. (Big ups to Katsuo).","My <em>calling card</em> is made of <em>rock</em>, which is a bit inconvenient because it is so big &amp; heavy. So I’m using a<strong> grindstone</strong> to grind it down in size.","シ、 テイ、 キイ、 チ","と、 といし、 と.ぐ、 みが.く","","研ぐ 【とぐ】 to sharpen, to hone, to whet, to grind, to wash (rice), to scour, to polish, to burnish<br>砥石 【といし】 whetstone, grindstone<br>青砥 【あおと】 medium-grade millstone<br>中砥 【なかと】 medium-grade millstone<br>砥石 【といし】 whetstone, grindstone<br>研ぐ 【とぐ】 to sharpen, to hone, to whet, to grind, to wash (rice), to scour, to polish, to burnish"],
碗:["石: stone; rock (RTK)　宛: address","teacup","BOWL, cup","<strong>Teacup</strong>s at the Japanese restaurant are usually made of stone and have the name and address of the restaurant written on them.","Similarly to the <a href=\"/study/kanji/%E6%A4%80\">椀</a> (<span class=\"frnr\">#2550</span>), the<strong> teacup</strong> made of <em>stone</em> has it's makers <em>address</em> carved into the bottom.","ワン","こばち","碗 【ワン】 bowl (ceramic, porcelain)<br>茶わん 【チャワン】 rice bowl, tea cup, teacup<br>お碗 【オワン】 bowl",""],
碍:["","obstacle","","Those gremlins! At <em>night break</em> they insist on coming out and <em>gluing</em> <em>stones</em> all over the place. These<strong> obstacle</strong>s make it nearly impossible for me to get to work!","You <a href=\"/study/kanji/%E5%BE%97\">得</a> (<span class=\"frnr\">#941</span>) 得 when you make forward progress. If you encounter a <em>rock</em>, you <em>cannot go</em> forward. Perhaps you can go round. This is an<strong> obstacle</strong>.","ガイ、 ゲ","さまた.げる","碍子 【ガイシ】 insulator<br>障害 【ショウガイ】 obstacle, impediment, hindrance, difficulty, barrier, handicap, impairment, disability, disorder, malfunction<br>妨害 【ボウガイ】 disturbance, obstruction, hindrance, jamming, interference<br>障害 【ショウガイ】 obstacle, impediment, hindrance, difficulty, barrier, handicap, impairment, disability, disorder, malfunction<br>無碍 【ムゲ】 free from obstacles",""],
