舵:["舟: boat　它: other","rudder","RUDDER, helm","A <em>house</em>hold <em>spoon</em> is used for the<strong> rudder</strong> of your model <em>boat</em>.","Let <em>house + sitting on the ground</em> = <em>cold beer</em> (because I like <em>sitting on the porch</em> under the shade of my <em>roof</em> drinking a <em>cold beer</em>. Also, I haven't used <em>cold beer</em> as a primitive yet, and surely that's blasphemy.) Story for <strong>rudder</strong>: The laconic fisherman heads upriver while relaxing in his <em>boat</em>, sitting back while the motor putts along, one hand on the<strong> rudder</strong>, the other on his <em>cold beer</em>.","ダ、 タ","かじ","舵手 【ダシュ】 helmsman, coxswain<br>舵柄 【カジヅカ】 helm, yoke<br>方向舵 【ホウコウダ】 rudder<br>昇降舵 【ショウコウダ】 elevator (aviation)","舵 【かじ】 rudder, helm<br>舵付き 【かじつき】 coxed (rowing), having a coxswain<br>面舵 【おもかじ】 starboard (side of a ship)<br>取り舵 【とりかじ】 port (side of a ship)"],
