錫:["","tin","","<strong>Tin</strong> is soft, bends easily, and melts at a low temperature. Hence<strong> tin</strong> is written as the <em>metal</em> that is <em>easy</em> to work with.","<em>Metal</em><strong> tin</strong> cans are sometimes far from <em>easy</em> to open.","セキ、 シャク","すず、 たま.う","錫杖 【シャクジョウ】 bishop's staff, khakkhara<br>錫杖草 【シャクジョウソウ】 yellow bird's-nest (Monotropa hypopitys), pinesap, false beechdrops<br>巡錫 【ジュンシャク】 preaching tour","錫 【すず】 tin (Sn)<br>錫石 【すずいし】 cassiterite<br>塩化錫 【えんかすず】 tin chloride<br>酸化錫 【さんかすず】 stannous oxide (SnO), stannic oxide (SnO2)"],
