馴:["馬: horse　巛: river (川); flood (RTK)","tame","BECOME TAME, get used to","The guy who said that you can take a <em>horse</em> to a <em>river</em>, but you can't make it drink obviously has never encountered a<strong> tame</strong> <em>horse</em>.","The process to getting a<strong> tame</strong> horse is a bit like getting a<strong> tame</strong> Christian - baptizization! you take it into the <em>river</em> at a young age (just after it's born is best) and dunk it in until it is almost drowned. Then at the last possible moment, when its life is flashing before its eyes (good baptizers know when this is), you pull it back above water. The first thing it sees is its \"rescuer\" and \"savior\", and it will be<strong> tame</strong> and follow you for the rest of its life.","ジュン、 シュン、 クン","な.れる、 な.らす、 したが.う","順化 【ジュンカ】 acclimatization, naturalization, acclimation<br>馴化 【ジュンカ】 acclimation<br>雅馴 【ガジュン】 refined (prose, etc.)","慣れる 【なれる】 to get used to, to grow accustomed to, to become familiar with, to become skilled in, to become experienced at, to become tame, to become domesticated<br>慣らす 【ならす】 to accustom, to train (e.g. one's ear), to tame, to domesticate, to train (e.g. an animal)<br>馴らす 【ならす】 to domesticate, to tame"],
