劫:["","kalpa","","<strong>kalpa</strong> is a Sanskrit word for a long period of time, sort of like \"aeon.\" Once a <strong>kalpa</strong> has <em>gone</em> (passed), there will be no more fossil fuels for <em>power</em>.","When a<strong> kalpa</strong> passes, all forms of <em>power</em> we see today will be <em>gone</em>.","コウ、 ゴウ、 キョウ","おびや.かす","劫 【コウ】 kalpa (eon, aeon), ko (in Go, the arrangement that allows for the eternal capture and recapture of the same stones)<br>劫火 【ゴウカ】 world-destroying conflagration<br>億劫 【オックウ】 troublesome, annoying<br>空劫 【クウコウ】 the kalpa of nothingness (the final aeon of the universe)<br>劫 【コウ】 kalpa (eon, aeon), ko (in Go, the arrangement that allows for the eternal capture and recapture of the same stones)<br>劫火 【ゴウカ】 world-destroying conflagration<br>永劫 【エイゴウ】 eternity, perpetuity<br>未来永劫 【ミライエイゴウ】 forevermore, for eternity<br>劫掠 【キョウリャク】 pillage, plunder","脅かす 【おびやかす】 to intimidate, to scare, to jeopardize, to endanger, to imperil"],
